\v 19 and tell the peopleÂŠ337696 inÂŠ337710 \add âthis country\add*, âMy masterÂŠ337701 YahwehÂŠ337701 saysÂŠ337700 this about the inhabitantsÂŠ337703 of YerushalemÂŠ337704, and the \add âcountry\add* of YisraelÂŠ337708, âThey'll anxiously eatÂŠ337711 their food and fearfully drinkÂŠ337714 their waterÂŠ337712, since \add âall the abundance from the land will be devastated\add* becauseÂŠ337719 of the violenceÂŠ337719 of all \add the people\add* who liveÂŠ337722 there.
\v 20 The inhabitedÂŠ337726 citiesÂŠ337725 will become desolateÂŠ337729, andÂŠ337725 the land \add itself\add* will become a wastelandÂŠ337727. ThenÂŠ337725 you'll know that I am YahwehÂŠ337735.â â â
\s1 Just because it never came true beforeâŠ
\rem /s1 A Popular Proverb and an Unpopular Message; A New Proverb for Israel
\p
\v 21 Then YahwehÂŠ337741 \add âgave me\add* \add another\add* messageÂŠ337739:
\v 22 âHumanity's child, what's that saying that youÂŠ337752 have in YisraelÂŠ337756? It goes, âThe daysÂŠ337759 \add âseem to go on and on, yet no prophecy ever comesÂŠ337760 true.\add*â
\v 23 So tell them, âThis is what the masterÂŠ337771 YahwehÂŠ337771 saysÂŠ337770: I'm going to prove that what they say isn'tÂŠ337778 correct, then they'll never say it againÂŠ337782 inÂŠ337783 YisraelÂŠ337783.â Tell them, âIt'll soon be the timeÂŠ337790 when everythingÂŠ337792 that the prophets have predicted will happen,
\v 24 because there'll no longer be any false visionsÂŠ337802 or \add âpeople-pleasing prophecies\add* within YisraelÂŠ337808.
\v 25 I speak, and I \add âput the words thatÂŠ337816 I speak into action\add*, because I am Yahweh. The matter will no longer be delayed, because I'll speak this messageÂŠ337818 inÂŠ337824 your \add âlifetimes\add*, \add you\add* rebelliousÂŠ337826 \add âpeople\add*, and then I'll carry it out!â That's the masterÂŠ337831 Yahweh'sÂŠ337813 declaration.â
\p
\v 26 Then YahwehÂŠ337838 \add âgave me\add* \add another\add* messageÂŠ337836:
\v 27 âListen, humanity'sÂŠ337844 child, the \add âIsraeliÂŠ337846 people\add* have saidÂŠ337849, âThe visionÂŠ337850 thatÂŠ337851 \add @the prophet\add* sees is for many yearsÂŠ337855 from now, and he prophesies about far-off timesÂŠ337857,â
\v 28 so tell them, âThe master YahwehÂŠ337867 says this: âMy wordsÂŠ337875 won'tÂŠ337869 be delayed any longer, butÂŠ337879 the messageÂŠ337878 thatÂŠ337876 I've given will be \add âput into effect\add*. That's the master Yahweh'sÂŠ337868 declaration.â â
\c 13
\s1 Condemning the false prophets
\rem /s1 Prophecy against False Male Prophets; False Prophets Condemned; Judgment against False Prophets
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehÂŠ337888 \add âgave me\add* \add another\add* messageÂŠ337886:
\v 2 âHumanity's child, prophesy againstÂŠ337896 the prophets who are prophesying in YisraelÂŠ337899, andÂŠ337901 tell those who are prophesying out of theirÂŠ337903 own imaginationsÂŠ337903, âListen to Yahweh'sÂŠ337907 messageÂŠ337905.
\v 3 My masterÂŠ337911 YahwehÂŠ337911 saysÂŠ337910 this: âFoolish prophetsÂŠ337916 who follow theirÂŠ337921 own spiritÂŠ337921 andÂŠ337922 haven't \add actually\add* seenÂŠ337923 any \add vision\add* \add âwon'tÂŠ337922 end well\add*.
\v 4 YisraelÂŠ337928, yourÂŠ337927 prophetsÂŠ337927 have been like jackalsÂŠ337925 inÂŠ337926 the wastelands.
\v 5 YouÂŠ337939 haven't gone to the breaks in the \add #walls\add* around the IsraeliÂŠ337938 \add cities\add* and repairedÂŠ337934 them, in order to \add âbe able to defend yourselves well during\add* the battleÂŠ337941 onÂŠ337933 Yahweh'sÂŠ337943 \add chosen\add* dayÂŠ337942.
\v 6 The people have false visions and make false predictions. Yahweh hasn't sentÂŠ337955 thoseÂŠ337949 who sayÂŠ337949 that they're bringing Yahweh'sÂŠ337952 declaration, \add âbutÂŠ337947 nevertheless they've made people hope that their messagesÂŠ337958 would come true\add*.
\v 7 Haven't you had false visionsÂŠ337961 and made false predictionsâall of you who say that you're bringing Yahweh'sÂŠ337971 declaration when I myself haven't spokenÂŠ337974?â
\p
\v 8 Therefore the master Yahweh says this, âBecause you \add people\add* have \add âpresented\add* falseÂŠ337986 visions and have told lies, this is the master Yahweh'sÂŠ337981 declaration againstÂŠ337989 you:
\v 9 \add âI'll punish\add* the prophetsÂŠ337998 who have lying visionsÂŠ337999 andÂŠ337994 who make falseÂŠ338002 predictions. They won'tÂŠ338005 be \add allowed\add* in the assembly of my peopleÂŠ338004, or enrolled in the record of Yisrael's \add âdescendants\add*. They mustn't goÂŠ338019 to the land of YisraelÂŠ338011â\add âthat's how\add* you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ338020 that I am the masterÂŠ338023 YahwehÂŠ338023.
\p
\v 10 Also becauseÂŠ338027 they led my peopleÂŠ338031 astrayÂŠ338028 and said, âPeace,â when there'sÂŠ338034 no peace, \add it's as if\add* they're buildingÂŠ338037 a wall and then whitewashingÂŠ338042 it.â\x + \xo 13:10: \xt Jer 6:14; 8:11.\x*
\v 11 Tell the ones who are whitewashingÂŠ338048 the wallÂŠ338060 that it'll fall down. There'll be a downpour, then I'll send hailstones to make it fall down, and a strong wind to breakÂŠ338060 it down.
\v 12 See, the wallÂŠ338064 will fall down. Haven't others \add âasked\add* you whereÂŠ338068 the whiteÂŠ338069 coating \add went\add* thatÂŠ338070 you put on it?
\p
\v 13 Therefore my masterÂŠ338077 YahwehÂŠ338077 says this: âIn my rage, I'llÂŠ338079 bring a storm, and inÂŠ338083 my angerÂŠ338086, there'll be \add âheavy rain causing floods\add*. In my rage, hailstones will completelyÂŠ338091 destroyÂŠ338091 \add @Yerushalem\add*.
\v 14 I'll tear down the wallÂŠ338096 that you covered withÂŠ338109 whitewashÂŠ338100, and I'll demolish it to ground level and expose itsÂŠ338109 foundationsÂŠ338106. SoÂŠ338093 it'll fall, and you'll be annihilated inÂŠ338109 the middle of it all. ThenÂŠ338093 you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ338110 that I am YahwehÂŠ338114.
\p
\v 15 In my rageÂŠ338119 I'll annihilate the wall andÂŠ338116 thoseÂŠ338129 who whitewashed it. I'll tell you, âThe wall doesn't exist anymore, nor do the people who whitewashed itâ
\v 16 those IsraeliÂŠ338132 prophets who prophesied about YerushalemÂŠ338138 and had visionsÂŠ338141 of peace for it. ButÂŠ338139 thereÂŠ338143 isn'tÂŠ338143 any peace! That'sÂŠ338133 the masterÂŠ338146 Yahweh'sÂŠ338147 declaration.â â
\rem /s1 Prophecy against False Female Prophets; Judgment against False Women Prophets
\p
\v 17 \add âSoÂŠ338151\add*, humanity'sÂŠ338153 child, \add âturn your attention to\add* your people'sÂŠ338159 daughtersÂŠ338158 and prophesy againstÂŠ338156 them \add âbecause they invented prophecies in theirÂŠ338161 own imaginationsÂŠ338161\add*.
\v 18 Tell \add >them\add* that the masterÂŠ338170 YahwehÂŠ338170 says this: âThe women \add âwon't end well\add* who sew magic charms onto every part of their handsÂŠ338180, and make headbands for people of \add âevery walk of life\add* \add that are used to deceive people and\add* hunt them down. \add Do you people really think you can get away with\add* hunting down my people, butÂŠ338165 thenÂŠ338165 save your own lives?
\v 19 You've profanedÂŠ338198 me among my people for handfulsÂŠ338204 of barleyÂŠ338205 and crumbs of breadÂŠ338207. \add âĄYou people have\add* killed people who shouldn't have died, and saved the lives of those who shouldn't have continued to live, because of your lies to my people who heard you.
\p
\v 20 Therefore my masterÂŠ338231 YahwehÂŠ338231 saysÂŠ338229 this: âI'm againstÂŠ338234 the magicÂŠ338236 charms thatÂŠ338237 you've used to \add âlure\add* the people in as if they were birds. Indeed, I'll tear them from your arms, and I'll let the people you've trapped like birds go free.
\v 21 I'llÂŠ338261 tear away your headbands andÂŠ338261 rescueÂŠ338265 my peopleÂŠ338268 from your \add âcontrol\add* so they'll no longer be trapped inÂŠ338274 your \add âsystem\add*. ThenÂŠ338261 you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ338276 that I am YahwehÂŠ338280.
\p
\v 22 BecauseÂŠ338282 you've discouraged the righteousÂŠ338286 people with lies (even though IÂŠ338288 didn'tÂŠ338289 desire their discouragement), and because you \add people\add* \add âencouraged the actions\add* of the wickedÂŠ338293 people instead so they won'tÂŠ338289 changeÂŠ338296 their waysÂŠ338297 to saveÂŠ338299 their livesÂŠ338299,
\v 23 \add âbecause of that\add*, you'll no longer have false visionsÂŠ338305 or continue to make predictions, because I'llÂŠ338310 rescueÂŠ338310 my peopleÂŠ338313 out of yourÂŠ338314 \add âcontrol\add*. Then you'll knowÂŠ338315 that I am YahwehÂŠ338319.â â
\c 14
\s1 Yahweh's hate for idols
\rem /s1 Idolaters Condemned; God's Judgments Justified; God Condemns Idolatry; The Idolatry of Israel's Leaders
\p
\v 1 \add âOne day\add* \add some\add* of the IsraeliÂŠ338325 eldersÂŠ338324 cameÂŠ338321 andÂŠ338326 sat down \add to talk\add*,
\v 2 andÂŠ338330 YahwehÂŠ338333 \add âgave\add* me this messageÂŠ338331:
\v 3 âHumanity's child, theseÂŠ338341 menÂŠ338340 have taken their idolsÂŠ338343 \add âto be their gods\add*, and \add âtheir choice to disobey makes it very difficult for them to relate to me\add*. Should I \add âeven let them ask me anything\add*?
\p
\v 4 Therefore tell them that the masterÂŠ338367 Yahweh says this: âEvery IsraeliÂŠ338372 person who \add âmakes their idols their priority\add*, or who \add âallows their disobedience to separate them from me\add*, and who then comesÂŠ338386 to a prophetÂŠ338389, I, Yahweh, will answerÂŠ338392 them according to \add âhow many idols they have\add*.
\v 5 I'll do that so that I can \add âreclaim the IsraeliÂŠ338403 people whose values are now far from mine due to\add* theirÂŠ338411 idolsÂŠ338410.
\p
\v 6 Therefore tell the IsraeliÂŠ338420 people that the masterÂŠ338423 YahwehÂŠ338423 saysÂŠ338422 this: â\add âChange your behaviour\add* and turn away from your idolsÂŠ338428. \add âMake a decision to stop disobeying me by doing those evil things\add*.
\p
\v 7 Any \add âIsraeliÂŠ338440 person\add* or any foreigner residing inÂŠ338445 YisraelÂŠ338440 who deserts me, who takes idolsÂŠ338449 \add âto be their gods\add* and \add âallows their disobedience to separateÂŠ338446 them from me\add*, and who then comesÂŠ338458 to a prophetÂŠ338461 to \add ârequest my guidance\add*, I, YahwehÂŠ338467, will answerÂŠ338468 that person myselfÂŠ338468.
\v 8 I'llÂŠ338473 \add âclearly show my disapproval\add* and make that personÂŠ338475 into a signÂŠ338478 \add for others\add* and into a \add âtalking point\add*, and they'll be \add âisolated from the rest of\add* my peopleÂŠ338482, and you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ338483 that I am YahwehÂŠ338487.
\p
\v 9 If a prophet is deceived and speaksÂŠ338494 a messageÂŠ338495, then I, YahwehÂŠ338497, will deceive that prophet. I'llÂŠ338502 \add âtake action\add* against him and destroyÂŠ338507 him \add to remove him\add* from amongÂŠ338508 the Israeli peopleÂŠ338509.
\v 10 \add âBoth the prophetÂŠ338517 and the one who asks him for advice will be guilty, and I'll punish both of them for theirÂŠ338513 disobedience.\add*
\v 11 Because of that, the IsraeliÂŠ338525 people will no longer wanderÂŠ338523 away from followingÂŠ338528 me, nor defile themselvesÂŠ338531 any longer through all their \add âdisobedience\add*. They'll be my people, and I'llÂŠ338540 be their godÂŠ338542. That's the masterÂŠ338544 Yahweh'sÂŠ338545 declaration.â â
\s1 Turning the country into wasteland
