\v 8 ButÂŠ341077 the nationsÂŠ341079 came against him from the surrounding provincesÂŠ341081.
\q1 They spreadÂŠ341082 their nets over himâ
\q1 he was caughtÂŠ341086 inÂŠ341085 their pit.
\q1
\v 9 With hooksÂŠ341090 \add in him\add*, they put him in a cage,
\q1 andÂŠ341088 thenÂŠ341088 they took him to the Babylonian kingÂŠ341094.
\q1 They took him to the fortresses
\q1 so that his voiceÂŠ341102 would no longer be heardÂŠ341101 in Yisrael's hills.
\b
\q1
\v 10 Your motherÂŠ341110 was like a vineÂŠ341111 plantedÂŠ341116 inÂŠ341112 your vineyardÂŠ341112 beside the water.
\q1 It was fruitfulÂŠ341117 and full of branchesÂŠ341118 becauseÂŠ341120 \add âthere was plenty\add* of water.
