\m That's a song for mourning, and should be sung as \add *such\add*.â
\c 20
\s1 Israeli rebellion
\rem /s1 The Rebellion of Israel; Rebellious Israel; The Lord's Will and Human Defiance; Israel's Continuing Rebellion
\p
\v 1 \add âSeven years\add* \add after we'd been taken to Babylon\add*, \add âsome\add* IsraeliÂŠ341195 eldersÂŠ341195 cameÂŠ341193 to \add âget me to ask YahwehÂŠ341200 for advice for them\add*.
\v 2 Then YahwehÂŠ341208 \add âgave\add* me \add this\add* messageÂŠ341206:
\v 3 âHumanity's child, tell the IsraeliÂŠ341218 eldersÂŠ341218 that the master Yahweh says this: âHave you \add people\add* come to \add âget advice from me\add*? As I live, I won't \add âallow you to ask for myÂŠ341232 advice\add*. That's the master Yahweh'sÂŠ341225 declaration.â
\p
\v 4 Will you judge them? Will you judge, humanity'sÂŠ341246 child? Let them know about theirÂŠ341250 ancestors' \add âdisgusting behaviour\add*.
\v 5 Tell them that the masterÂŠ341258 Yahweh says this: âOn the dayÂŠ341260 that I choseÂŠ341261 YisraelÂŠ341262 andÂŠ341253 made myselfÂŠ341268 knownÂŠ341268 to them inÂŠ341262 EgyptÂŠ341271, I raised myÂŠ341273 hand to \add âmake a promise\add* to Yakov's descendantsÂŠ341265. I told \add >them\add*, âI am Yahweh your godÂŠ341278â\x + \xo 20:5-6: \xt Exo 6:2-8.\x*â
\v 6 on that dayÂŠ341280 I raised my handÂŠ341283 to \add âmake a promise\add* to them that I would bringÂŠ341285 them out of EgyptÂŠ341287 into a land that I'd carefully selectedÂŠ341293 for them. It was flowingÂŠ341295 with milkÂŠ341296 and honeyÂŠ341297âitÂŠ341299 was the most beautifulÂŠ341298 of all the landsÂŠ341302.
\v 7 I told them, âLet each \add âfamily\add* throwÂŠ341309 away their EgyptianÂŠ341311 idolsÂŠ341310, plusÂŠ341310 \add âany other detestableÂŠ341307 thingsÂŠ341307 they have\add*. Don'tÂŠ341312 \add âdefile\add* yourselvesÂŠ341314. I am YahwehÂŠ341316 yourÂŠ341317 godÂŠ341317.â
\v 8 \add âButÂŠ341319\add* they rebelledÂŠ341319 againstÂŠ341321 me andÂŠ341319 were unwilling to listenÂŠ341324 to me. \add *They\add* didn'tÂŠ341322 throw away the detestableÂŠ341329 thingsÂŠ341329 \add âthey had\add* or abandonÂŠ341338 theirÂŠ341330 Egyptian idolsÂŠ341335, so I determined to pour my fury out onÂŠ341321 them to satisfy my rageÂŠ341341 among them \add âright there\add* inÂŠ341321 EgyptÂŠ341336.
\v 9 I \add âdid thatÂŠ341357 to protect my reputationÂŠ341352\add* so it wouldn't be \add âtarnished\add* inÂŠ341360 the eyesÂŠ341355 of the nationsÂŠ341356 \add âwhere theyÂŠ341359 were staying\add*. I made myselfÂŠ341362 \add âclearly\add* knownÂŠ341362 to them\f + \fr 20:9 \ft them: Probably referring to those countries, but some translations interpret it to refer to the ones being brought out.\f* by bringingÂŠ341365 them out of EgyptÂŠ341367.
\p
\v 10 \add âSoÂŠ341369\add* IÂŠ341372 led them out of EgyptÂŠ341371 andÂŠ341369 took them into the wildernessÂŠ341375.
\v 11 ThenÂŠ341377 IÂŠ341385 gaveÂŠ341377 them my instructionsÂŠ341381 andÂŠ341377 regulationsÂŠ341381â\add âanyone who follows\add* them will liveÂŠ341391.\x + \xo 20:11-13: \xt Lev 18:5.\x*
\v 12 I also \add âestablished rest days\add* as a signÂŠ341401 between myself andÂŠ341403 themâfor them to knowÂŠ341404 that I am YahwehÂŠ341407 who \add âdeclares them different from others\add*.\x + \xo 20:12: \xt Exo 31:13-17.\x*
\v 13 \add âButÂŠ341410 the IsraeliÂŠ341413 people\add* rebelledÂŠ341410 againstÂŠ341412 me in the wilderness. They \add âwouldn't follow my instructionsÂŠ341417\add*, andÂŠ341410 they rejectedÂŠ341424 my regulationsÂŠ341417, \add even though\add* whoever obeys them will live. They severelyÂŠ341438 disrespected my rest days, so I said I'd pour my fury out onÂŠ341412 them in the wilderness in order to end them.
\v 14 \add âButÂŠ341443 I did thatÂŠ341450 to protect my reputationÂŠ341445\add* so it wouldn't be \add âtarnished\add* in the eyesÂŠ341448 of the nationsÂŠ341449, in whose sightÂŠ341452 I had broughtÂŠ341451 them out \add of Egypt\add*.
\v 15 SoÂŠ341454 I myself \add âtook action by making a promise\add* to them inÂŠ341460 the wildernessÂŠ341460 not to bringÂŠ341462 them into the land thatÂŠ341467 I'd been going to give themâa land flowingÂŠ341470 withÂŠ341460 milkÂŠ341471 andÂŠ341454 honeyÂŠ341472, whichÂŠ341467 was the most beautifulÂŠ341473 out of all the landsÂŠ341477.\x + \xo 20:15: \xt Num 14:26-35.\x*
\v 16 I promised that because they'd rejectedÂŠ341481 my instructionsÂŠ341484 and not \add âfollowed my regulationsÂŠ341484\add*, and they disrespected my rest days, because \add âwhat they really wanted was\add* their idolsÂŠ341495.
\v 17 \add âButÂŠ341499\add* I pitied them, so I didn'tÂŠ341502 \add âwipe them out\add* inÂŠ341508 the wildernessÂŠ341508.
\p
\v 18 I told their childrenÂŠ341513 inÂŠ341514 the wildernessÂŠ341514, âDon'tÂŠ341517 \add âfollow yourÂŠ341516 parents' habits or behaviour\add*, andÂŠ341510 don'tÂŠ341517 defile yourselvesÂŠ341529 withÂŠ341514 their idolsÂŠ341526.
\v 19 I am YahwehÂŠ341532 yourÂŠ341533 godÂŠ341533â\add âfollow my instructionsÂŠ341534, obey my regulationsÂŠ341534\add*,
\v 20 and keepÂŠ341546 my rest days \add different from other days\add* so that they'll be a signÂŠ341548 between me and you. \add That way\add* you'll all knowÂŠ341551 that I am YahwehÂŠ341554 yourÂŠ341555 godÂŠ341555.â
\p
\v 21 \add âHowever\add*, their sons andÂŠ341557 daughters rebelledÂŠ341557 against me. They didn'tÂŠ341562 \add âkeep my instructionsÂŠ341561 or follow my regulationsÂŠ341561\add*, \add even though\add* whoever obeys them will liveÂŠ341577. They disrespected my rest days, so I determined to pour my fury out onÂŠ341559 them to satisfy my rageÂŠ341585 against them inÂŠ341559 the wildernessÂŠ341590.
\v 22 \add âButÂŠ341592 I didn'tÂŠ341599 proceed, for the sake of my reputationÂŠ341598\add*, so it wouldn't be mocked by the nationsÂŠ341602 \add âwho saw me\add* bring the Israelis out \add of Egypt\add*.
\v 23 \add âSo I took action\add* inÂŠ341617 the wildernessÂŠ341617, \add promising that instead\add* I would scatterÂŠ341618 them among the nationsÂŠ341620 and disperseÂŠ341621 them into other countriesÂŠ341623.\x + \xo 20:23: \xt Lev 26:33.\x*
\v 24 I decided to do that since they hadn't obeyed my instructionsÂŠ341630, and since they'd rejectedÂŠ341631 my regulationsÂŠ341630 and disrespected my rest daysâ\add âthey really wanted\add* their ancestors' idolsÂŠ341637.
\p
\v 25 ThenÂŠ341642 I even gaveÂŠ341645 them instructionsÂŠ341647 that weren't goodÂŠ341649, andÂŠ341650 regulationsÂŠ341647 that theyÂŠ341652 couldn't liveÂŠ341652 by.
\v 26 I declared them to be defiledÂŠ341655 \add âbecause of the giftsÂŠ341657 they gave\add* (they sacrificed everyÂŠ341659 \add âwoman's\add* firstbornÂŠ341661 child inÂŠ341657 the fire) so that I could fill them withÂŠ341657 horror so they would knowÂŠ341667 that I am YahwehÂŠ341670.â
\rem /s1 Judgment and Restoration
\p
\v 27 Therefore, humanity'sÂŠ341681 child, speakÂŠ341674 to the \add âIsraeliÂŠ341677 people\add* andÂŠ341682 tell them that the masterÂŠ341686 YahwehÂŠ341686 saysÂŠ341685 this: âThat was also how yourÂŠ341692 ancestorsÂŠ341692 blasphemedÂŠ341690 me when theyÂŠ341690 were unfaithfulÂŠ341695 to me.
\v 28 WhenÂŠ341697 I broughtÂŠ341697 them into the land thatÂŠ341701 I'd promised to giveÂŠ341706 them, thenÂŠ341697 whenever they sawÂŠ341709 any highÂŠ341713 hill and leafyÂŠ341717 treeÂŠ341716, they offered their sacrificesÂŠ341723. They provokedÂŠ341727 me with their offerings, and also burnt their fragrant incense there and pouredÂŠ341733 out their drinkÂŠ341737 offerings.
\v 29 ThenÂŠ341739 I \add âasked\add* them, âWhat's this high place whereÂŠ341743 you present your offerings?â so the place is calledÂŠ341748 BamahÂŠ341750 \add (meaning âHigh placeâ)\add* to this dayÂŠ341752.â
\rem /s1 Judgment and Restoration
\p
\v 30 Therefore tell the \add âIsraeliÂŠ341760 people\add* that the masterÂŠ341764 YahwehÂŠ341764 \add âasks\add* this: âWhy do you \add âdefile yourselvesÂŠ341769\add* withÂŠ341766 your ancestorsÂŠ341767' customs? Why do you act like prostitutesÂŠ341773, searching for disgusting thingsÂŠ341771?
\v 31 To this dayÂŠ341787, when you offer up your giftsÂŠ341776 (\add offering\add* your sons \add âas burnt sacrifices\add*), you defile yourselvesÂŠ341781 withÂŠ341775 all your idolsÂŠ341784. SoÂŠ341775 why shouldÂŠ341789 I let you \add âtry to find me, you IsraeliÂŠ341791 people\add*? As I live, I won't allow you \add people\add* to \add ârequest myÂŠ341795 help or advice\add*. That's the masterÂŠ341797 Yahweh'sÂŠ341798 declaration.
\v 32 The thought that'sÂŠ341811 forming in yourÂŠ341807 mind will never happen. You \add people\add* say, âLet's be like the other nationsÂŠ341816âlike the clansÂŠ341817 in other \add âcountriesÂŠ341818\add* who worship wood andÂŠ341821 stoneÂŠ341821.â
\s1 Punishment and forgiveness
\rem /s1 God Will Restore Israel; God Punishes and Forgives
\p
\v 33 This is the masterÂŠ341827 Yahweh'sÂŠ341828 declaration: As I live, I'llÂŠ341838 certainly reignÂŠ341838 over you \add people\add* with \add âstrict control\add*, and with fury that'll be pouredÂŠ341837 out onÂŠ341832 you.
\v 34 I'll bringÂŠ341841 you out from the other \add âpeopleÂŠ341845 groups\add* andÂŠ341841 will gatherÂŠ341846 you out of the countriesÂŠ341850 where you've been scatteredÂŠ341852. I'll do this withÂŠ341853 \add âpower, pouringÂŠ341859 out fury\add*.
\v 35 ThenÂŠ341861 I'll bringÂŠ341861 you into the wildernessÂŠ341865 of the \add âpeopleÂŠ341866 groups\add*, andÂŠ341861 thereÂŠ341869 I'll judgeÂŠ341867 you face to faceâ
\v 36 just like I judged yourÂŠ341879 ancestorsÂŠ341879 inÂŠ341880 the Egyptian wildernessÂŠ341880, that's how I'llÂŠ341884 judge youÂŠ341885 \add people\add*. That's the masterÂŠ341887 Yahweh'sÂŠ341888 declaration.
\p
\v 37 I'll cause you \add people\add* to passÂŠ341890 underÂŠ341892 my staff \add to be counted\add*, andÂŠ341894 I'll make you obey the requirements of \add &our\add* agreementÂŠ341897.
\v 38 I'll purgeÂŠ341899 the rebelsÂŠ341901 from among you, as well as those who revolt againstÂŠ341903 me. I'll send them out from the land whereÂŠ341905 they're staying \add as foreigners\add*, butÂŠ341899 they won'tÂŠ341912 enter YisraelÂŠ341911. ThenÂŠ341899 you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ341914 that I am YahwehÂŠ341918.
\p
\v 39 SoÂŠ341920 to you \add âIsraeliÂŠ341921 people\add*, the masterÂŠ341928 YahwehÂŠ341928 says this: âEach of you should go to his own idols. Worship them if you refuse to listenÂŠ341938 to me, butÂŠ341920 you mustÂŠ341938 no longer desecrate my sacredÂŠ341943 name withÂŠ341948 your giftsÂŠ341948 andÂŠ341920 your idols,
\v 40 because this is the masterÂŠ341960 Yahweh'sÂŠ341961 declaration: all the \add âIsraeliÂŠ341957 people\add* will worship me there onÂŠ341952 my sacredÂŠ341983 mountain inÂŠ341952 YisraelÂŠ341958. I'llÂŠ341973 be happy to acceptÂŠ341971 your offeringsÂŠ341980 there, along withÂŠ341952 your choiceÂŠ341979 giftsÂŠ341980 \add âdedicated to me\add*.
\v 41 I'll acceptÂŠ341987 you like a soothingÂŠ341986 aromaÂŠ341985 when I bringÂŠ341989 you out from the \add âpeopleÂŠ341993 groups\add* and gatherÂŠ341994 you out of the countriesÂŠ341998 where you've been scatteredÂŠ342000. I'll \add âdisplay my holiness\add* among you for the nationsÂŠ342005 to see.
\v 42 You'll knowÂŠ342007 that I am YahwehÂŠ342011 when I bringÂŠ342012 youÂŠ342013 \add back\add* to YisraelÂŠ342017âto the land that I promised to giveÂŠ342026 to yourÂŠ342028 ancestorsÂŠ342028.
\v 43 There you'll \add âcall to mind\add* your conduct and \add âeverything you defiled yourselves by doing\add*, and you'll despise yourselves for all the evilÂŠ342047 things you'veÂŠ342041 doneÂŠ342049.
\v 44 ThenÂŠ342051 you'll knowÂŠ342051 that I am Yahweh, when I doÂŠ342056 this to you for the sake of my \add âreputationÂŠ342059\add*, not because of your evilÂŠ342062 practicesÂŠ342063, andÂŠ342063 not because of your corruptÂŠ342064 actions, \add âyou IsraeliÂŠ342065 people\add*. That's the masterÂŠ342068 Yahweh'sÂŠ342055 declaration.â â
\s1 The burnt forest
\rem /s1 Prophecy Against the South; A Prophecy against the Negeb; Judgment against the Negev; Fire in the South
\p
\v 45 Then Yahweh \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* message:
\v 46 âHumanity's child, \add âlook\add* towards the southern lands, and speak against the southâprophesy against the Negev forest.
\v 47 Tell the forest that this is the master Yahweh's declaration: See, I'll set a fire among you. It'll burn up every \add âtree among you, whether living or dead\add*. The fiery flame won't \add be able to\add* be put outâevery \add âarea\add* from the north to the south will be burnt.
\v 48 Then \add âeveryone\add* will see that I am Yahweh, when I light the fire, and it can't be extinguished.â â
\p
\v 49 Then I said, âOh no, my master Yahweh, now they're \add âwondering if I'm just someone who tells\add* \add cute\add* parables.â
\c 21
\s1 Yahweh's piercing sword
\rem /s1 The Lord's Sword; The Lord's Sword of Judgment; Babylon, God's Sword of Judgment; The Drawn Sword of God; Threats against sinners
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehÂŠ342076 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ342074:
\v 2 âHumanity's child, \add âlook\add* towards Yerushalem, and speak against the sacred places and prophesyÂŠ342092 against Yisrael.
