\v 35 So the masterÂŠ343742 YahwehÂŠ343742 saysÂŠ343741 this, âBecause you'veÂŠ343745 forgottenÂŠ343745 me and thrownÂŠ343747 me away behindÂŠ343749 your back, you'll bear the consequences of your shameful behaviour and your prostitutionÂŠ343758.â â
\s2 Revealing the disgusting deeds of the sisters
\rem /s1 God's Judgment on Both Sisters; The Lord's Judgment on Both Sisters
\p
\v 36 YahwehÂŠ343762 saidÂŠ343761 to me, âHumanity's child, will youÂŠ343767 judgeÂŠ343767 OholahÂŠ343770 and OholibahÂŠ343773? Present them \add a list of\add* theirÂŠ343777 disgusting actions,
\v 37 since they've committed adultery, and also have bloodÂŠ343781 onÂŠ343782 their handsÂŠ343782. They've committed adultery \add âby worshipping\add* their idols, and they've even caused their sons to pass throughÂŠ343795 the fire \add to be considered\add* as food for their idols.
\v 38 Then \add âon top of that\add*, they defile my sanctuaryÂŠ343806, and \add âat the same time\add*, they disrespect my rest days.
\v 39 WhenÂŠ343814 they'd slaughteredÂŠ343814 their childrenÂŠ343817 for their idolsÂŠ343818, thenÂŠ343814 they cameÂŠ343819 to my sanctuaryÂŠ343822 onÂŠ343814 the same dayÂŠ343823 to desecrate itÂŠ343825. SoÂŠ343814 listen, that's what they've done \add âright there inÂŠ343814 my residence\add*.
\p
\v 40 You sent messengersÂŠ343840 \add to go and bring\add* menÂŠ343836 from far away. Now look, they indeed cameÂŠ343845âthoseÂŠ343846 who you \add prepared for by\add* bathing, paintingÂŠ343848 your eyesÂŠ343849, and adorningÂŠ343850 yourselfÂŠ343850 with jewellery.
\v 41 You satÂŠ343853 on a lovely couchÂŠ343856 bed with a tableÂŠ343858 arrangedÂŠ343859 \add âin front of you\add* where you placed my incenseÂŠ343861 andÂŠ343853 my \add olive\add* oilÂŠ343862.
\v 42 ThenÂŠ343866 the soundÂŠ343866 of a noisy crowdÂŠ343867 was around herÂŠ343869 as all kinds of menÂŠ343872, even SabeansÂŠ343876, were broughtÂŠ343875 inÂŠ343869 from the wildernessÂŠ343878, and theyÂŠ343879 put braceletsÂŠ343880 on their handsÂŠ343883 and beautifulÂŠ343885 crownsÂŠ343884 on their headsÂŠ343888.
\v 43 ThenÂŠ343890 I saidÂŠ343890 about \add âthat experienced adultererÂŠ343892\add*, âNow they'll \add âtreat herÂŠ343897 as a prostituteÂŠ343895\add*, andÂŠ343898 she'll fornicateÂŠ343897 with them.â
\v 44 They \add âhad sex with\add* her like men do with a prostituteÂŠ343906. In that way theyÂŠ343908 \add âhad sex with\add* the two immoral womenÂŠ343915, OholahÂŠ343911 andÂŠ343912 OholibahÂŠ343914.
\v 45 \add âButÂŠ343918\add* righteousÂŠ343919 men will \add âjudgeÂŠ343921\add* and punish them as adulteresses, and they'll punish them withÂŠ343932 the \add appropriate\add* sentence for those who've shed blood, becauseÂŠ343928 they're adulteresses plusÂŠ343925 they have blood onÂŠ343932 theirÂŠ343932 handsÂŠ343932.
\p
\v 46 So the masterÂŠ343938 YahwehÂŠ343938 saysÂŠ343937 this: I'll bringÂŠ343940 a groupÂŠ343942 \add to attack\add* \add @Shomron and Yerushalem\add* and give them up to be terrorizedÂŠ343945 and plunderedÂŠ343946.
\v 47 ThenÂŠ343948 that groupÂŠ343951 will stoneÂŠ343948 them with stones and cut them down with their swordsÂŠ343954. They'll killÂŠ343957 their \add âchildren\add* and burnÂŠ343960 down their housesÂŠ343958.
\v 48 \add That's how\add* I'llÂŠ343962 remove shameful behaviour from the land, andÂŠ343962 discipline all the womenÂŠ343970 so they'll no longer act like prostitutes.
\v 49 They'll use your shameful behaviour against you. You'll all bear the guilt of the sinsÂŠ343978 you did with your idolsÂŠ343979, andÂŠ343975 in that way you'll knowÂŠ343981 that I am the masterÂŠ343984 YahwehÂŠ343984.â
\c 24
