\v 15 Then YahwehÂŠ344234 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ344232:
\v 16 âListen, humanity'sÂŠ344240 child, I'm taking your \add âcherished wife\add* from you withÂŠ344248 a plague, butÂŠ344249 you mustn't mournÂŠ344252 or weep, or let any tearsÂŠ344255 \add âshow\add*.
\v 17 You mustÂŠ344269 groan silentlyÂŠ344259. Don'tÂŠ344262 \add âorganise\add* a funeral \add âwhen she's\add* deadÂŠ344260. Put onÂŠ344270 your turbanÂŠ344265 and your sandalsÂŠ344268, butÂŠ344268 don'tÂŠ344262 veil your beard, or eatÂŠ344279 the breadÂŠ344276 of men who mournÂŠ344261 who've lost their wives.â
\p
\v 18 \add âSoÂŠ344281\add* I spokeÂŠ344281 to the peopleÂŠ344284 in the morning, andÂŠ344281 thenÂŠ344281 my wifeÂŠ344287 diedÂŠ344286 in the eveningÂŠ344288. In the morning I didÂŠ344289 what I'd been commandedÂŠ344292 to do.
\v 19 ThenÂŠ344294 the peopleÂŠ344296 asked me, âWon't you tell us what theseÂŠ344303 things meanâthe \add âway that you'reÂŠ344306 behaving\add*?â
\p
\v 20 âYahwehÂŠ344313 \add âgave me\add* a messageÂŠ344311,â I answered them,
\v 21 âto tell the \add âIsraeliÂŠ344320 people\add* that the masterÂŠ344325 YahwehÂŠ344325 saysÂŠ344324 this to them: Listen, I'll desecrate my sanctuaryÂŠ344331âthe prideÂŠ344332 of your powerÂŠ344333, the delight of your eyesÂŠ344335, and the yearning of your soulÂŠ344337âand \add also\add* your sonsÂŠ344338 and daughtersÂŠ344339 who youÂŠ344341 left behind \add there inÂŠ344342 Yerushalem\add* will be killed by the swordÂŠ344342.
\v 22 \add âWhenÂŠ344345 that happens,\add* you \add peopleÂŠ344354\add* will doÂŠ344345 exactly as I'veÂŠ344347 doneÂŠ344347: you won'tÂŠ344351 veil your beards, or eatÂŠ344356 the breadÂŠ344353 of mourning men,
\v 23 \add âbutÂŠ344358 instead\add* your turbansÂŠ344358 will be on your headsÂŠ344361, and your sandalsÂŠ344362 on your feetÂŠ344363. You won'tÂŠ344364 mournÂŠ344367 or weep, because you'll melt away \add âdue to your disobedience\add*, and everyone will groanÂŠ344370 for \add âtheir relatives\add*.
\v 24 \add âSoÂŠ344376\add* Yehezkel will be a signÂŠ344379 for you, becauseÂŠ344387 when that time comesÂŠ344385, you'll doÂŠ344384 \add âexactly the same as he's doing\add*. ThenÂŠ344376 you \add people\add* will knowÂŠ344386 that I am the masterÂŠ344389 YahwehÂŠ344389.â â
\p
\v 25 âButÂŠ344393 you, humanity'sÂŠ344396 child, on the dayÂŠ344398 that I capture their temple, (which is their joyÂŠ344404, their pride, and what they see and desireÂŠ344408), and when I takeÂŠ344399 away their sonsÂŠ344414 and daughtersÂŠ344415,
\v 26 a refugee will comeÂŠ344419 to you here on that dayÂŠ344417 to give you the newsÂŠ344422.
\v 27 At that time, yourÂŠ344428 mouthÂŠ344428 will be openedÂŠ344427 up to that refugee and you'll speakÂŠ344432 \add againÂŠ344435\add*âyou'll no longer be silent. You'll be a signÂŠ344438 for them so that they'll knowÂŠ344439 that I am YahwehÂŠ344443.â
