\v 8 He'll killÂŠ344884 your daughters inÂŠ344883 the countrysideÂŠ344882. He'll set up a siegeÂŠ344887 program and buildÂŠ344888 a ramp against your walls and liftÂŠ344891 up shieldsÂŠ344893 against you.
\v 9 He'll use his batteringÂŠ344896 rams to \add âsmash down\add* your wallsÂŠ344898, andÂŠ344895 he'll tear down your towersÂŠ344899 withÂŠ344898 his axesÂŠ344901.
\v 10 \add âThey'll have\add* so many horsesÂŠ344904 that their dust will coverÂŠ344905 youÂŠ344905. Your walls will shakeÂŠ344911 withÂŠ344913 the noiseÂŠ344907 of \add their\add* horsemen, wagonsÂŠ344909, and chariotsÂŠ344910. When he \add ârides through\add* your gatesÂŠ344914, he'll \add pick his way over the stones\add* like men do when enteringÂŠ344913 a cityÂŠ344916 whose walls have been brokenÂŠ344917 down.
