\v 12 They'll tear down your wallsÂŠ344940 and destroy your nice homesâplunderingÂŠ344935 your riches and looting your merchandiseÂŠ344938. ThenÂŠ344935 they'll throw your \add building\add* stonesÂŠ344944, wood, and rubble into the \add âocean\add*.
\v 13 I'llÂŠ344951 stop the soundÂŠ344954 of your songsÂŠ344953, andÂŠ344951 the \add âmusic\add* from your harpsÂŠ344955 won'tÂŠ344956 be heardÂŠ344957 anymore.
\v 14 I'llÂŠ344960 make you \add back into\add* a bare rockâyou'll become a placeÂŠ344963 where nets are spreadÂŠ344963 \add out to dry\add*. You'll never be builtÂŠ344967 againÂŠ344968, becauseÂŠ344969 I, master Yahweh, have spokenÂŠ344972. That's the master Yahweh'sÂŠ344971 declaration.
\rem /s1 The Effect of Tyre's Destruction
\p
\v 15 The masterÂŠ344980 YahwehÂŠ344980 saysÂŠ344979 this to Tsor, âWon't the islandsÂŠ344993 shake with the soundÂŠ344985 of yourÂŠ344986 downfallÂŠ344986, and with the groansÂŠ344987 of the woundedÂŠ344988 when the terrible slaughterÂŠ344990 is happening inÂŠ344987 youÂŠ344991?
\v 16 ThenÂŠ344995 all the \add âleaders of the coastal kingdoms\add* will step down from their thronesÂŠ344997 and removeÂŠ345001 their robesÂŠ345004 and take off their embroideredÂŠ345008 clothes. \add Instead,\add* they'll clothe themselves in fear, they'll sitÂŠ345016 on the ground and trembleÂŠ345010 every momentÂŠ345018, and they'll be appalledÂŠ345019 because of youÂŠ345020.
\v 17 ThenÂŠ345022 they'll \add âsing this song of mourning\add* for you andÂŠ345022 say to you,
