\v 18 âHumanity's child, the Babylonian KingÂŠ346348 Nebuchadnetstsar stationed his army to do hard work against \add the fortified island city of\add* Tsor \add (TyreÂŠ346359)\add*. Every headÂŠ346362 was rubbed until it was made bald, and everyÂŠ346360 shoulderÂŠ346366 was made raw. Yet he and his army received no payment from Tsor for the hard work thatÂŠ346378 he carried out against it,
\v 19 therefore the masterÂŠ346387 YahwehÂŠ346387 saysÂŠ346386 this, âListen, I'm giving EgyptÂŠ346398 to the Babylonian KingÂŠ346392 Nebuchadnetstsar and he'll takeÂŠ346403 away its wealthÂŠ346400, plunderÂŠ346404 its possessions, and carryÂŠ346399 off everything he finds thereâthat will be his army's wages.
\v 20 I'veÂŠ346414 givenÂŠ346414 him the land of EgyptÂŠ346419 as the wages for the work theyÂŠ346421 did for me. That's the masterÂŠ346424 Yahweh'sÂŠ346425 declaration.
\p
\v 21 On that dayÂŠ346428 I'll make \add âpower\add* sprout up for the \add âkingdom\add* of YisraelÂŠ346433, and I'll \add âput youÂŠ346434 amongÂŠ346439 them to speak out\add* so they'll knowÂŠ346440 that I am YahwehÂŠ346444.â â
