\v 11 He and his army with him, the terror of nationsÂŠ346593, will be broughtÂŠ346594 in to destroyÂŠ346595 the land. They'll draw out theirÂŠ346598 swordsÂŠ346598 against EgyptÂŠ346601 and fillÂŠ346602 the land with those they killÂŠ346595.
\v 12 I'll make the rivers into dry groundÂŠ346610, and I'll sell the land into the hands of wickedÂŠ346617 men. I'll make the land and itsÂŠ346620 abundant \add produce\add* desolateÂŠ346618 by the actions of strangersÂŠ346623. I, YahwehÂŠ346625, have spokenÂŠ346626.
