\v 20 \add âAt the beginning of May\add* in the eleventh yearÂŠ346736 \add since King Yoyakin (Jehoiachin) had been taken captive\add*,\f + \fr 30:20 \ft (Back in time to) 587 B.C.\f* YahwehÂŠ346743 \add âgave me\add* a messageÂŠ346741:
\v 21 âHumanity's child, I'veÂŠ346757 brokenÂŠ346757 the Egyptian kingÂŠ346754 Far-oh's arm. Listen, it hasn't been \add âput inÂŠ346769 a splint\add*, or set to heal withÂŠ346769 a bandageÂŠ346765, so that it'll become strongÂŠ346767 enough \add again\add* to hold a swordÂŠ346769.
\v 22 Therefore the masterÂŠ346777 YahwehÂŠ346777 saysÂŠ346775 this, âListen, I'm againstÂŠ346780 the Egyptian kingÂŠ346783 Far-oh and I'll breakÂŠ346786 both his strongÂŠ346792 arm and the \add previously\add* brokenÂŠ346795 one, and I'll make the sword fall from his \add âgrip\add*.
\v 23 ThenÂŠ346802 I'llÂŠ346807 scatterÂŠ346802 EgyptÂŠ346805 among the \add other\add* nationsÂŠ346806 andÂŠ346807 disperseÂŠ346807 \add @their people\add* among the landsÂŠ346808.
