\r (Eze. 3:16-21)
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehÂŠ347878 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ347876:
\v 2 âHumanity's childÂŠ347888, tell this to your people: âWhen I \add âsend an army\add* against any \add âcountry\add*, then the people of that \add âcountry chooseÂŠ347899 one of theirÂŠ347905 men to become\add* a watchmanÂŠ347909 for them.
\v 3 He looks for \add âany attacker comingÂŠ347915 onto\add* the land, andÂŠ347911 thenÂŠ347911 he blowsÂŠ347919 his horn to warnÂŠ347921 the peopleÂŠ347924.
\v 4 If the people hearÂŠ347926 the soundÂŠ347930 of the horn butÂŠ347926 don'tÂŠ347932 \add âtake any notice\add*, and if the \add âattacker\add* comesÂŠ347934 and kills them, thenÂŠ347926 each one's bloodÂŠ347937 is onÂŠ347938 their own headÂŠ347938.
\v 5 \add Yes,\add* if someone heardÂŠ347944 the horn \add âbut paid no attention\add*, \add @that person's\add* bloodÂŠ347947 is on them, \add âbut\add* if \add @those people\add* \add âdo pay attention\add*, they'll save their own lives.
\v 6 \add âHowever,\add* if the watchman sees the \add âattacker\add* comingÂŠ347962, \add âbut\add* doesn't blow the horn, \add âthat is, if\add* the peopleÂŠ347967 weren't warnedÂŠ347970, and if the \add âattacker approaches\add* and takes anyone'sÂŠ347975 life, thenÂŠ347955 that person dies inÂŠ347966 their own sin, \add âbut\add* I'llÂŠ347983 requireÂŠ347983 their bloodÂŠ347979 from the watchman.â
\p
\v 7 Now, \add âtalking to\add* you, humanity'sÂŠ347989 child: I'veÂŠ347991 made you a watchmanÂŠ347990 for the \add âIsraeliÂŠ347993 people\add*. You'll hearÂŠ347994 the words from my mouthÂŠ347995 and then warnÂŠ347997 them on my behalf.
\v 8 If I say to a wicked person, âYou wicked person, you're certainly about to die,â and if you don'tÂŠ348006 announce it so as to warn that wicked \add person\add* about their behaviour, then that wicked \add person\add* will die inÂŠ348013 their sin, butÂŠ348006 \add âit'll be you that I hold responsible for their death\add*.
\v 9 \add âButÂŠ348019\add* if you warn the wickedÂŠ348023 person about their behaviour, so that they might turn back from it, andÂŠ348019 if that person doesn't turn back from their behaviour, thenÂŠ348019 they'll die inÂŠ348032 their sin, butÂŠ348019 you yourself will have saved your own lifeÂŠ348035.
\s1 Each person is responsible for their own deeds
