\p
\v 10 \add âSo,\add* humanity'sÂŠ348042 child, youÂŠ348049 tell the \add âIsraeliÂŠ348046 people\add*, âYou're saying this, âOur errors and our disobedience \add âhave come back on us and they're hurting\add* us. How can we go on living \add like this\add*?â â
\v 11 Tell them that this is the masterÂŠ348070 Yahweh'sÂŠ348071 declaration: âAs I live, I don't delight inÂŠ348075 the deathÂŠ348075 of wicked people. If they turn away from their wicked behaviour, then they'll live! \add âSo turn back\add*, \add yes\add* turn away from your wicked behaviour. Why should you \add âIsraeliÂŠ348090 people\add* dieÂŠ348089?â
\p
\v 12 \add âSo now\add*, humanity'sÂŠ348097 childÂŠ348101, you tell your people, âRighteous people's righteousness won't saveÂŠ348107 them if they sin. Wicked people's wickednessÂŠ348111 won't cause them to die if they turn away from their sin. \add âNo,\add* the righteous person won't be able to liveÂŠ348122 because of his righteousness if he sinsÂŠ348125.
\v 13 If I say that a righteous person will surely live, and if they trust inÂŠ348145 their righteousness and then commit injusticeÂŠ348145, I won'tÂŠ348143 call to mind any of \add âthe good things they did\add*âthat person will dieÂŠ348150 for the wickedness they committed.
\v 14 \add âAgain,\add* if I say to the wickedÂŠ348153, âYou will surelyÂŠ348154 die,â butÂŠ348152 if they thenÂŠ348152 turn away from their sins and do what's just and rightÂŠ348160,
\v 15 \add âlike\add* returningÂŠ348163 loan guarantees that were wickedly demanded, or \add âlike\add* making restitution for what they've stolen, and then if they \add âobey the instructionsÂŠ348167\add* that give lifeÂŠ348168 and no longer \add âdisobey\add*, then \add @those formerly wicked people\add* will surely liveâthey won'tÂŠ348170 dieÂŠ348176.
\v 16 None of the sinsÂŠ348180 thatÂŠ348182 they've committed will be called to mind against them. Those who've acted justly and rightlyÂŠ348188, will certainlyÂŠ348190 live.
\p
\v 17 ButÂŠ348193 your peopleÂŠ348195 say, âThe master'sÂŠ348199 way isn'tÂŠ348196 fair!â butÂŠ348193 it's your ways that aren'tÂŠ348196 fair.
\v 18 When the righteous \add >person\add* turnsÂŠ348206 away from \add âdoing what's right\add* and \add âbecomes disobedient\add*, then they'll dieÂŠ348212 inÂŠ348213 \add @theirÂŠ348213 sinÂŠ348213\add*.
\v 19 WhenÂŠ348215 the wickedÂŠ348216 \add >person\add* turnsÂŠ348215 away from \add âdoing evil\add* and does what's just and rightÂŠ348220, they'll liveÂŠ348223 because of those things.
\v 20 \add âYes,\add* you people sayÂŠ348225, âThe master'sÂŠ348229 wayÂŠ348228 isn'tÂŠ348226 fair!â \add butÂŠ348225\add* I'llÂŠ348232 judgeÂŠ348232 each of you \add âIsraeliÂŠ348234 people\add* accordingÂŠ348231 to \add âyour behaviour\add*.â
