\v 21 In \add âmid-January\add* of the twelfth yearÂŠ348241 of ourÂŠ348245 captivity \add inÂŠ348239 Babylon\add*, \add âsomeone who'd escapedÂŠ348249\add* from YerushalemÂŠ348250 \add (Jerusalem)\add* cameÂŠ348246 to me andÂŠ348238 told me that the cityÂŠ348253 had been captured.\x + \xo 33:21: \xt 2Ki 25:3-10; Jer 39:2-8; 52:4-14.\x*
\v 22 YahwehÂŠ348257 had \add âheld me inÂŠ348260 a vision\add* the eveningÂŠ348260 before the fugitiveÂŠ348263 came, \add âbutÂŠ348255\add* my mouth was opened by the time he came to me atÂŠ348260 dawn, \add âso by thenÂŠ348255, IÂŠ348276 was able to speak againÂŠ348277\add*.
