\v 23 Then YahwehÂŠ348283 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ348281:
\v 24 âHumanity's child, the people inhabitingÂŠ348290 those ruinsÂŠ348291 \add back\add* in YisraelÂŠ348296 \add (IsraelÂŠ348296)\add* are sayingÂŠ348297, âAbrahamÂŠ348301 was only one person, and he inherited the land, \add âbutÂŠ348302 there's lots of us\add* \add now\add*. The land has been givenÂŠ348309 to us as an inheritance.â
\p
\v 25 Therefore tell them that the masterÂŠ348321 YahwehÂŠ348321 says this: You eat blood, and you \add âpay your respect to\add* your idolsÂŠ348332, then you pour out people's blood. Should you then inherit that land?
\v 26 You \add people\add* \add ârely\add* on your swordsÂŠ348341 \add for protection\add*, and you've doneÂŠ348342 disgusting thingsâeach man defilesÂŠ348349 his neighbour'sÂŠ348348 wifeÂŠ348347. Should you \add really\add* possessÂŠ348351 that land?â
\p
\v 27 Tell them thatÂŠ348381 the masterÂŠ348361 YahwehÂŠ348361 saysÂŠ348360 this: As I live, surely the ones in the ruinsÂŠ348370 will be killed by swordsÂŠ348371, and I'llÂŠ348379 giveÂŠ348379 those in the countrysideÂŠ348377 to the \add âwild animalsÂŠ348378\add* as food, and those in fortresses and in cavesÂŠ348383 will dieÂŠ348385 of plaguesÂŠ348384.
\v 28 ThenÂŠ348387 I'llÂŠ348387 turn the \add âcountry\add* into a desolationÂŠ348391 and a horror, and the prideÂŠ348394 \add âthat came from itsÂŠ348395 power\add* will endÂŠ348393, because Yisrael'sÂŠ348398 mountainsÂŠ348397 will be desertedÂŠ348396, and there'll be no one to \add âwalk\add* through them.â
\v 29 ThenÂŠ348402 they'll knowÂŠ348402 thatÂŠ348417 I am YahwehÂŠ348406, when I make the \add âcountry\add* a desolationÂŠ348411 andÂŠ348402 a wastelandÂŠ348412 becauseÂŠ348403 of all the \add âdisgusting things\add* they've doneÂŠ348418.
