\p
\v 30 So now humanity'sÂŠ348424 childÂŠ348425, yourÂŠ348426 peopleÂŠ348426 are out besideÂŠ348429 the wallsÂŠ348430 and the gates of their housesÂŠ348432 talkingÂŠ348427 about youÂŠ348428, and they're all telling each other, âLet's go and listenÂŠ348447 to the prophet's messageÂŠ348449 thatÂŠ348450 comesÂŠ348450 from YahwehÂŠ348452.â
\v 31 SoÂŠ348454 my people will come to you, as they often do, and will sit inÂŠ348472 frontÂŠ348460 of you and listenÂŠ348462 to your words, but they won'tÂŠ348467 obey them. The right words are \add âonÂŠ348472 their lips\add*, but their heartsÂŠ348477 are goingÂŠ348478 afterÂŠ348475 unjustÂŠ348476 profit.
\v 32 \add âYes,\add* you're like a lovely song to them, a beautifulÂŠ348484 sound that's played well on a stringed instrument, so they'll listenÂŠ348488 to yourÂŠ348491 wordsÂŠ348491, butÂŠ348480 none of them will obey them.
\v 33 SoÂŠ348496 when all that happens, watch out, \add becauseÂŠ348500 itÂŠ348498 will indeed\add* happen. ThenÂŠ348496 they'll \add ârealise\add* that a prophet'sÂŠ348501 been amongÂŠ348503 them.â
