\p
\v 11 \add âSo\add* the masterÂŠ348713 YahwehÂŠ348713 saysÂŠ348712 this: Listen, I myself will searchÂŠ348718 for \add those lost from\add* my flockÂŠ348721, and I \add âĄmyself\add* will look after them,
\v 12 like a shepherdÂŠ348725 searches for his sheepÂŠ348732 when he's amongÂŠ348730 his scattered flock. So I'll look for my flock and I'll rescueÂŠ348739 them from all the placesÂŠ348743 whereÂŠ348744 theyÂŠ348745 were scattered \add âduring the darkÂŠ348749 times\add*.
\v 13 I'll bring \add @my peopleÂŠ348754\add* out from among the \add ânations\add*. I'll gatherÂŠ348755 them from \add foreign\add* landsÂŠ348758 and bring them \add back\add* to theirÂŠ348762 land. I'll put them in pastures onÂŠ348768 Yisrael's mountainsidesÂŠ348766, by the streams, and in every settlement in the land.
\v 14 I'llÂŠ348776 put them in good pasturesâYisrael's high mountainsÂŠ348778 will be theirÂŠ348783 grazing places. They'll lie down thereÂŠ348784 in places good for grazing, in abundant pastures, and they'll grazeÂŠ348790 onÂŠ348778 Yisrael's hills.
\v 15 I myself will shepherdÂŠ348797 my flockÂŠ348798, andÂŠ348799 I myself will \add âgive them rest\add*. That's the masterÂŠ348802 Yahweh'sÂŠ348803 declaration.
\p
\v 16 I'll searchÂŠ348808 out the lost and restore the outcast. I'll bandage up those who are broken and heal those who are sickÂŠ348817, butÂŠ348809 I'll destroyÂŠ348825 those who are fat and well. I will shepherdÂŠ348826 withÂŠ348827 justiceÂŠ348827.
\p
\v 17 SoÂŠ348829 now this is what the masterÂŠ348833 YahwehÂŠ348833 says, You, my flockÂŠ348830, listen, I'll be a judgeÂŠ348836 between one sheep and another, and between rams and billy goatsÂŠ348842.
\v 18 Isn't it enoughÂŠ348844 to feed onÂŠ348852 the good pasture? Do you have to trampleÂŠ348851 down \add âany remaining grass\add*? Or drinkÂŠ348856 from clearÂŠ348853 watersÂŠ348855, then muddyÂŠ348860 the streams withÂŠ348852 your feet?
\v 19 Must my flockÂŠ348862 eat what you've trampledÂŠ348863 andÂŠ348862 drinkÂŠ348868 what you've muddied with your feet?
\p
\v 20 Therefore the masterÂŠ348874 YahwehÂŠ348874 says this to them: Listen, I myself will judgeÂŠ348880 between the fat sheep and the thin ones,
\v 21 because you \add shepherds\add* have pushed them with your sides and shouldersÂŠ348891, and you've gored all the weak ones with your hornsÂŠ348893 untilÂŠ348898 you \add succeeded inÂŠ348890\add* scatteringÂŠ348900 them away from the land.
