\v 3 Tell it that the masterÂŠ349090 YahwehÂŠ349090 saysÂŠ349089 this: Listen, I'm against you \add Edom, represented by\add* MtÂŠ349094. SeirÂŠ349096, and I'llÂŠ349097 \add âwork against you to\add* make you a desolationÂŠ349101 and a wasteÂŠ349102.
\v 4 I'llÂŠ349106 \add âturn\add* yourÂŠ349104 cities into ruins, and you yourself will become desolateÂŠ349108. Then you'll knowÂŠ349110 that I am YahwehÂŠ349114.
\p
\v 5 You'veÂŠ349126 always been hostile to the IsraeliÂŠ349124 peopleÂŠ349124, and when they were distressed you \add âdecided to attack them withÂŠ349132 swordsÂŠ349131\add*âatÂŠ349132 the time theirÂŠ349133 punishmentÂŠ349135 was coming to an end.
\v 6 Therefore, this is the masterÂŠ349143 Yahweh'sÂŠ349144 declaration: As I live, I'llÂŠ349148 prepareÂŠ349148 you for bloodshed, and bloodshed will chase after you. Since you didn'tÂŠ349153 hate bloodshed, bloodshed will \add âcome to\add* you.
\v 7 I'llÂŠ349159 make \add âEdom\add* completely desolateÂŠ349165 when I cut \add âit off so that no one will want to pass throughÂŠ349168 it\add*.
\v 8 I'llÂŠ349171 fillÂŠ349171 its mountainÂŠ349174 \add ranges\add* withÂŠ349185 people who were killedâthoseÂŠ349181 killed by the swordÂŠ349183 will fall onÂŠ349185 your high hillsÂŠ349176 and valleysÂŠ349177 and inÂŠ349185 all your streams.
\v 9 I'llÂŠ349189 make \add âyourÂŠ349190 land perpetuallyÂŠ349188 desolate\add*. Your citiesÂŠ349190 won'tÂŠ349191 be inhabited, and then you'll knowÂŠ349194 that I am YahwehÂŠ349198.
\p
\v 10 You've saidÂŠ349201, âThese two nationsÂŠ349205 and these two landsÂŠ349209 will become mine, and we'll possessÂŠ349212 them,â even when YahwehÂŠ349213 was thereÂŠ349214 with them.
\v 11 Therefore, this is the masterÂŠ349222 Yahweh'sÂŠ349223 declaration: As I live, I'll act according to your angerÂŠ349225 and according to your jealousyÂŠ349226 thatÂŠ349227 you had inÂŠ349230 your hatredÂŠ349229 of Yisrael, and I'll show myselfÂŠ349231 to them when I judgeÂŠ349234 youâ
\v 12 thenÂŠ349236 you'll knowÂŠ349236 thatÂŠ349248 I am YahwehÂŠ349240. I'veÂŠ349241 heardÂŠ349241 all the insults you spoke against Yisrael's \add âhill country\add*, when you saidÂŠ349249, âThey've been destroyedâthey've been givenÂŠ349259 over to us to devour.â
\v 13 You raised yourselvesÂŠ349262 up against me withÂŠ349264 what you said, and you multipliedÂŠ349265 the wordsÂŠ349267 you said against me, and I heardÂŠ349269 all of them.
\p
\v 14 TheÂŠ349275 masterÂŠ349274 YahwehÂŠ349274 saysÂŠ349273 this: I'llÂŠ349281 make youÂŠ349283 \add âinto a desolateÂŠ349280 place\add* while the \add ârest of the world cheers\add*.
\v 15 Just like you rejoicedÂŠ349285 over the IsraeliÂŠ349287 people's inheritanceÂŠ349286 \add âwhen it was made desolate\add*, I'llÂŠ349295 doÂŠ349295 the same to you. You'll become a desolation, MtÂŠ349300. SeirÂŠ349302 and all of EdomÂŠ349305âall of it. Then they'll knowÂŠ349307 that I am YahwehÂŠ349311.â
\c 36
\s1 God's blessing for Yisrael (Israel)
\rem /s1 Blessing on Israel; A Prophecy to the Mountains of Israel; Restoration for Israel; God's Blessing on Israel
\p
\v 1 âNow, humanity'sÂŠ349317 child, prophesyÂŠ349318 to Yisrael's mountains and sayÂŠ349323, âMountains of Yisrael, listenÂŠ349326 to Yahweh'sÂŠ349329 messageÂŠ349327.
\v 2 The masterÂŠ349333 YahwehÂŠ349333 saysÂŠ349332 this: The enemyÂŠ349337 has saidÂŠ349336, âAha,â \add when talking\add* about youÂŠ349338, andÂŠ349340 âThe ancient \add âhilltop shrines\add* have becomeÂŠ349343 ours.â â
\p
\v 3 Therefore prophesyÂŠ349347 and tell them that the masterÂŠ349351 YahwehÂŠ349351 saysÂŠ349350 this: Because of your desolationÂŠ349355 and becauseÂŠ349353 of the attacks that came onÂŠ349354 you from all sidesÂŠ349358, you've \add âended up belonging to\add* other nationsÂŠ349362âyou've been the subject of slanderousÂŠ349368 lips and tonguesÂŠ349367, and of people'sÂŠ349370 stories.
\v 4 Therefore, mountains of YisraelÂŠ349374, listenÂŠ349375 to the messageÂŠ349376 from the master Yahweh: The master Yahweh says this to the mountains and the high hillsÂŠ349386, to the streambeds and valleysÂŠ349388, to the \add âplacesÂŠ349389 that have been destroyed and are now uninhabited\add*, and to the forsaken citiesÂŠ349391 that have becomeÂŠ349394 plunderÂŠ349395 and a subject of mocking for the other nationsÂŠ349398 that surround themâ
\v 5 the masterÂŠ349407 YahwehÂŠ349407 saysÂŠ349406 this: I'veÂŠ349414 certainly spokenÂŠ349414 in the \add âheat\add* of my anger against the other nationsÂŠ349418, against EdomÂŠ349421 and everyoneÂŠ349433 who took my land for themselves as a possessionÂŠ349431âagainst all those who had both celebration in their heartÂŠ349435 and disdain in their spirit as they seized my land so they could claim itsÂŠ349439 pasturelandsÂŠ349439 for themselves.â
\p
\v 6 Therefore, prophesyÂŠ349443 to YisraelÂŠ349447 and tell the mountainsÂŠ349449 and the high hillsÂŠ349450, the streambeds and the valleysÂŠ349452, that the masterÂŠ349457 YahwehÂŠ349457 saysÂŠ349455 this: Listen, in my fury and in my angerÂŠ349461 I'm declaring this becauseÂŠ349463 you'veÂŠ349466 endured insultsÂŠ349464 from \add other\add* nationsÂŠ349465.
\v 7 Therefore, the masterÂŠ349471 YahwehÂŠ349471 saysÂŠ349470 this: I myself will \add âtake action and promise\add* that the nationsÂŠ349481 that surround youÂŠ349483 will certainly \add be made to\add* carry theirÂŠ349486 own shame.
\v 8 ButÂŠ349490 you Israeli mountainsÂŠ349491, you'll grow branchesÂŠ349493 andÂŠ349495 bear fruitÂŠ349495 for my Israeli peopleÂŠ349497, since they'll soon comeÂŠ349501 back to you,
\v 9 because, listen, I'mÂŠ349504 for you, and I'llÂŠ349506 treat you favourablyâyou'll be ploughed and sown \add with seed\add*.
\v 10 I'llÂŠ349511 multiplyÂŠ349511 \add âyour populationâall the IsraeliÂŠ349517 people\add*. The citiesÂŠ349520 will be inhabitedÂŠ349519 \add again\add* andÂŠ349511 the ruinsÂŠ349521 rebuiltÂŠ349522.
\v 11 I'll increaseÂŠ349528 \add both\add* people and animalsÂŠ349527 on you \add âĄmountains\add* so that they'll multiplyÂŠ349524 and be fruitfulÂŠ349529. ThenÂŠ349524 I'll causeÂŠ349530 you to be inhabitedÂŠ349530 like you were previously, and I'll make you prosper more than you did in the past \add âso that\add* you'll knowÂŠ349535 that I am YahwehÂŠ349539.
\v 12 I'llÂŠ349541 bring my Israeli peopleÂŠ349546 to walkÂŠ349541 on you. They'll possessÂŠ349548 you, and you'll be their inheritanceÂŠ349551, and you'll no longer causeÂŠ349541 their children to die.
\p
\v 13 The masterÂŠ349561 YahwehÂŠ349561 saysÂŠ349560 this: They're telling you, âYou \add âĄmountains\add* devourÂŠ349566 peopleÂŠ349564, bereavingÂŠ349570 your nationÂŠ349571 of children,â
\v 14 therefore you won'tÂŠ349577 consume people any longer, and you'll no longer make your nationÂŠ349581 mourn their deaths. That's the masterÂŠ349589 Yahweh'sÂŠ349590 declaration.
\v 15 I won'tÂŠ349592 allow you to hear the insultsÂŠ349597 from the \add other\add* nationsÂŠ349598 any longerâyou'll no longer have to bear the peopleÂŠ349600 groups shaming you, andÂŠ349592 you won't causeÂŠ349609 your nationÂŠ349605 to stumbleÂŠ349609. That's the masterÂŠ349612 Yahweh'sÂŠ349613 declaration.â
\rem /s1 The Renewal of Israel; Israel's New Life
\p
\v 16 Then YahwehÂŠ349619 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ349617:
\v 17 âHumanity's child, when the \add âIsraeliÂŠ349626 people\add* inhabited their land, they defiledÂŠ349632 it withÂŠ349634 their customs and their activities. \add âIn myÂŠ349640 eyes,\add* their customs were like the uncleannessÂŠ349636 of a woman's menstruationÂŠ349637,
\v 18 \add âso\add* I poured out my fury against them for the bloodÂŠ349647 thatÂŠ349648 they'd poured out onÂŠ349654 the land, andÂŠ349642 for how they'd polluted itÂŠ349655 withÂŠ349654 theirÂŠ349654 idolsÂŠ349654.
\v 19 I scatteredÂŠ349657 them among the nationsÂŠ349659âtheyÂŠ349660 were dispersedÂŠ349660 through the landsÂŠ349661. I judgedÂŠ349664 them according to their customs andÂŠ349657 their actions.
\v 20 ThenÂŠ349666 they went to those \add other\add* nationsÂŠ349669, andÂŠ349666 whereverÂŠ349670 they went, they profanedÂŠ349674 my holy nameÂŠ349677 when people asked about them, âAre theseÂŠ349684 really Yahweh'sÂŠ349683 people? After all, they've been thrown out of his land.â
\v 21 \add âButÂŠ349688\add* IÂŠ349696 had compassion for my holy nameÂŠ349691 thatÂŠ349693 the \add âIsraeliÂŠ349695 people\add* had defiled amongÂŠ349697 the \add other\add* nationsÂŠ349697, when theyÂŠ349700 went thereÂŠ349701.
\p
\v 22 Therefore tell the \add âIsraeli people\add* thatÂŠ349725 the masterÂŠ349711 YahwehÂŠ349711 saysÂŠ349710 this: I'm not doing this for the sake of you \add âIsraeli people\add*, but for my sacredÂŠ349724 nameÂŠ349722, whichÂŠ349725 you've profanedÂŠ349726 amongÂŠ349727 the nationsÂŠ349727 everywhere you've gone.
\v 23 My greatÂŠ349737 nameÂŠ349736, whichÂŠ349740 you \add people\add* have profaned among the nations, I'llÂŠ349733 make holy \add even\add* among the nations \add where\add* you profaned it. ThenÂŠ349733 the nations will know thatÂŠ349740 I am Yahweh, when they see you recognise my holinessÂŠ349733. That's the masterÂŠ349750 Yahweh'sÂŠ349748 declaration.
\v 24 I'll takeÂŠ349756 you \add back\add* out of those nationsÂŠ349760 and gatherÂŠ349761 you from every land, and I'll bringÂŠ349766 you into your land.
\v 25 ThenÂŠ349772 I'll sprinkleÂŠ349772 pure waterÂŠ349774 on you so you'll be cleanedÂŠ349776 from all of your impuritiesÂŠ349778, andÂŠ349772 I'll purifyÂŠ349782 you from all your idolsÂŠ349781.
\v 26 I'll give you \add people\add* a new heart and a new spiritÂŠ349789 inÂŠ349792 your innermostÂŠ349792 partsÂŠ349792, and I'll take the stony heart away from your \add âbodies\add* and \add âreplace it withÂŠ349792\add* a heart of flesh.\x + \xo 36:26-28: \xt Eze 11:19-20.\x*
\v 27 I'llÂŠ349807 put my spirit inÂŠ349808 you and enable you \add IsraelisÂŠ349809\add* to \add âfollow my instructionsÂŠ349813 and keepÂŠ349816 my regulationsÂŠ349813\add*.
\v 28 ThenÂŠ349819 you'll inhabit the land thatÂŠ349821 I gaveÂŠ349822 to your ancestorsÂŠ349823âyou'll be my peopleÂŠ349826 andÂŠ349819 I'llÂŠ349828 be your godÂŠ349830.
\v 29 I'll saveÂŠ349832 you from all of your uncleannessÂŠ349835, and thenÂŠ349832 I'll summonÂŠ349836 the grainÂŠ349839 and multiply itâI'll no longer \add âassign\add* famineÂŠ349846 to you.
\v 30 I'llÂŠ349848 multiply the \add #fruit onÂŠ349862 the trees\add* andÂŠ349853 the produceÂŠ349853 \add âfrom the soil\add* so that you'll no longer \add âbe shamed by other nationsÂŠ349862 seeing you suffering\add* famineÂŠ349861.
\v 31 ThenÂŠ349864 you'll think about your wicked customsÂŠ349867 and your activities thatÂŠ349870 weren't goodÂŠ349873, and \add âyour facesÂŠ349875 will display your loathingÂŠ349874 of your own sins and your disgusting habits\add*.
\v 32 ButÂŠ349892 make sure you know this: I'm not doing all that for \em your\em* sake, \add âso you IsraeliÂŠ349894 people\add* shouldÂŠ349889 be ashamedÂŠ349891 andÂŠ349892 disgraced because of your \add âbehaviour\add*. That's the masterÂŠ349887 Yahweh'sÂŠ349888 declaration.
\p
\v 33 The masterÂŠ349900 YahwehÂŠ349900 saysÂŠ349899 this: \add âWhen\add* I purify you from all your disobedience, I'llÂŠ349907 enable you to inhabitÂŠ349907 the citiesÂŠ349910 \add again\add* and to rebuildÂŠ349911 the ruined placesÂŠ349912,
\v 34 andÂŠ349914 the idle land will be tilledÂŠ349916 until it's no longer a wasteland for everyoneÂŠ349922 to see as they go past.
\v 35 ThenÂŠ349926 \add instead\add* they'll say, âThis land was desolateÂŠ349935, butÂŠ349926 it's becomeÂŠ349930 like the gardenÂŠ349931 of EdenÂŠ349933âthe abandoned cities and the uninhabited ruins that were torn down are now fortifiedÂŠ349938 and inhabited.â
\v 36 ThenÂŠ349941 the other nationsÂŠ349942 aroundÂŠ349945 youÂŠ349945 will knowÂŠ349941 thatÂŠ349943 I am Yahweh, becauseÂŠ349946 I built up the ruins and replanted the abandoned placesÂŠ349953. I, Yahweh, have declared it and I will do it.
\p
\v 37 The masterÂŠ349962 YahwehÂŠ349962 \add also\add* saysÂŠ349961 this: The \add âIsraeliÂŠ349969 people\add* will againÂŠ349964 ask me to do this for them: to increaseÂŠ349972 \add âtheir population like sheep\add*.
\v 38 Just like the flock \add âthat's kept separate to be used\add* for sacrifices (like the flock inÂŠ349981 YerushalemÂŠ349980 atÂŠ349981 itsÂŠ349981 scheduled feastsÂŠ349981), so too the ruinedÂŠ349985 citiesÂŠ349984 will be filled withÂŠ349981 flocks of people andÂŠ349989 theyÂŠ349983 will knowÂŠ349989 that I am YahwehÂŠ349993.â
\c 37
\s1 The valley with bleached bones
\rem /s1 A Valley of Dry Bones; The Valley of Dry Bones
\p
\v 1 \add âOneÂŠ350003 day YahwehÂŠ350000 gave me another vision\add*, and he took me out by his spiritÂŠ350002 and put me down inÂŠ350002 the middleÂŠ350005 of a valleyÂŠ350006 that was full of bonesÂŠ350009.
\v 2 ThenÂŠ350011 he led me all around them, and wow, there were so many bonesÂŠ350017 in the valleyÂŠ350022, and they were totally dried out!
\v 3 âHumanity's child,â he \add âasked\add* me, âcan theseÂŠ350034 bonesÂŠ350033 become living \add people\add* again?â
\p âMy masterÂŠ350036 YahwehÂŠ350036,â I \add âreplied\add*, â\add âonly you would knowÂŠ350039 that\add*.â
\p
\v 4 ThenÂŠ350041 he told me, âProphesy over theseÂŠ350047 bones andÂŠ350041 tell them, âDry bones. Listen to Yahweh'sÂŠ350055 messageÂŠ350053.
\v 5 The masterÂŠ350059 YahwehÂŠ350059 saysÂŠ350058 this to theseÂŠ350062 bonesÂŠ350061: Listen, I'm aboutÂŠ350065 to put breathÂŠ350067 into you, andÂŠ350068 you'll liveÂŠ350068.
\v 6 I'll \add âconnect\add* sinews to you and put fleshÂŠ350075 onto you. I'll coverÂŠ350076 you withÂŠ350080 skin and put breathÂŠ350081 into you so you'll liveÂŠ350082. ThenÂŠ350070 you'll knowÂŠ350083 that I am YahwehÂŠ350087.â â
\p
\v 7 SoÂŠ350089 I prophesiedÂŠ350089 as I was instructedÂŠ350091, andÂŠ350089 wow, a soundÂŠ350094 like something rattlingÂŠ350098 started as the bonesÂŠ350100 moved togetherÂŠ350099âbone against bone!
\v 8 I lookedÂŠ350106 and, wow, the bones now had sinews onÂŠ350119 them, and fleshÂŠ350111 grew up \add over that\add*, and thenÂŠ350106 skin coveredÂŠ350113 them! \add âButÂŠ350106\add* thereÂŠ350118 was still no breath inÂŠ350119 them.
\p
\v 9 ThenÂŠ350121 Yahweh told me, âProphesy to the wind. Humanity's child, prophesy and tell the air, âThe masterÂŠ350140 Yahweh \add âcommands\add* this: Breath, come from the four \add âcompass points\add*, and breatheÂŠ350146 into theseÂŠ350148 who've been killedÂŠ350147, so they'll \add âcome to life\add*.â â
\p
\v 10 \add âSoÂŠ350151\add* I prophesiedÂŠ350151 just like I was commandedÂŠ350153. Then breathÂŠ350156 came into them andÂŠ350151 they \add âcame to lifeÂŠ350157\add*. Then they stoodÂŠ350158 on theirÂŠ350161 feetÂŠ350161âa very largeÂŠ350163 army.
\p
\v 11 Then Yahweh \add âinformed\add* me, âHumanity's child, theseÂŠ350175 bones are the entireÂŠ350176 \add âIsraeliÂŠ350178 population\add*. Listen, they're sayingÂŠ350182, âOur bones have driedÂŠ350183 up and our hope is gone. We've been cut off.â
\v 12 Therefore prophesyÂŠ350191 and tell them, âThe masterÂŠ350197 YahwehÂŠ350197 says this: Listen, I'll open your graves and lift you, my peopleÂŠ350208, out from them, then I'll bring you back to YisraelÂŠ350214.
\v 13 Then, my peopleÂŠ350229, when I open your graves and bringÂŠ350226 you out of them, you'll knowÂŠ350217 that I am YahwehÂŠ350221.
\v 14 I'll placeÂŠ350235 my spirit within you so you'll liveÂŠ350234, and I'll cause you to rest inÂŠ350233 your land when you knowÂŠ350240 that I am Yahweh. I declare it, and I will do it. That is Yahweh'sÂŠ350244 declaration.â â
\s1 The two sticks indicating unity of Yisrael and Yehudah
\rem /s1 One Nation Under One King; The Two Sticks; Reunion of Israel and Judah; Judah and Israel in One Kingdom
\p
\v 15 Then YahwehÂŠ350255 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ350253:
\v 16 â\add âSoÂŠ350259 now\add*, humanity'sÂŠ350262 child, take a stick for yourselfÂŠ350265 and write on it, âFor YehudahÂŠ350270 and for all their associated people.â ThenÂŠ350259 take another stick and write on it, âFor \add YisraelÂŠ350272\add* (\add represented by\add* YosefÂŠ350280 \add (Joseph)\add*, the branch of EfrayimÂŠ350282), and for all their associated people.â
\v 17 ThenÂŠ350290 hold both of them together so that theyÂŠ350299 \add âseem like\add* one stickÂŠ350297 inÂŠ350301 yourÂŠ350301 handÂŠ350301.
\v 18 WhenÂŠ350303 your peopleÂŠ350307 \add âask you andÂŠ350303 insist\add*, âAren't you going to tell us what theseÂŠ350315 props of yours mean?â
\v 19 then tell them, âThe masterÂŠ350323 YahwehÂŠ350323 says this: Look, I'm taking Yosef's branch that's in Efrayim'sÂŠ350335 hand along withÂŠ350333 the tribesÂŠ350336 of YisraelÂŠ350337 hisÂŠ350338 companionsÂŠ350338, and joining it to YehudahÂŠ350346's branch, so that they'll make one branch, and they'll become one in my hand.â
\p
\v 20 Hold the branches inÂŠ350360 yourÂŠ350360 handÂŠ350360 thatÂŠ350356 youÂŠ350358 wrote onÂŠ350360 \add âwhile theyÂŠ350354 watched\add*.
\v 21 Tell \add @the people\add*, âThe masterÂŠ350368 YahwehÂŠ350368 says this: Look, I'm aboutÂŠ350372 to take the IsraeliÂŠ350375 people out from the nationsÂŠ350378 whereÂŠ350379 they went. I'llÂŠ350383 gatherÂŠ350383 them from the surrounding lands andÂŠ350363 bringÂŠ350386 them \add back\add* to theirÂŠ350390 land.
\v 22 I'llÂŠ350392 \add âunite them as a single\add* nation inÂŠ350397 the land, onÂŠ350397 the mountainsÂŠ350397 of YisraelÂŠ350398, and there'll be one king as king over all of them, and they'll no longer be two nationsâthey'll no longer be dividedÂŠ350412 into two kingdomsÂŠ350415.
\v 23 ThenÂŠ350418 they'll no longer defile themselvesÂŠ350419 with their idolsÂŠ350421, with their disgusting thingsÂŠ350422, or with any of their other sins. I'll saveÂŠ350425 them from all of their faithless actions\f + \fr 37:23 \ft The Hebrew text has âliving placesâ rather than âfaithless actionsâ (from the Septuagint), but it's difficult to make sense of the Hebrew.\f* with whichÂŠ350429 they've sinnedÂŠ350430, and I'll purify them so they'll be my peopleÂŠ350437 and I'll be their godÂŠ350441.
\v 24 My servantÂŠ350443 DavidÂŠ350444 will be kingÂŠ350445 over them, \add âso\add* there'll be one shepherdÂŠ350447 over them all, and they'll \add âfollow\add* my instructionsÂŠ350453 and keepÂŠ350454 my regulationsÂŠ350453 and obey them.\x + \xo 37:24: \xt Eze 34:24.\x*
\v 25 They'll live in the land thatÂŠ350462 I've given to my servant Yakov \add (Jacob, also called Yisrael/Israel)\add*, where your ancestorsÂŠ350470 had stayed. They'll live in it foreverÂŠ350484âthey, their childrenÂŠ350474, and their grandchildren, and my servant DavidÂŠ350480 will be their \add âpermanentÂŠ350479\add* leader.
\v 26 I'll establish a peaceÂŠ350489 treaty with themâa never-ending agreementÂŠ350488 with them. I'll establish them and multiplyÂŠ350495 them and put my sacred place amongÂŠ350501 them foreverÂŠ350502.
\v 27 My residence will be with themâI'llÂŠ350507 be their godÂŠ350509, andÂŠ350504 they'll be my peopleÂŠ350514.\x + \xo 37:27: \xt 2Cor 6:16; Rev 21:3.\x*
\v 28 ThenÂŠ350516 the \add other\add* nationsÂŠ350517 will knowÂŠ350516 that IÂŠ350519 am YahwehÂŠ350520 who sets YisraelÂŠ350524 apart, when my sacred place is \add âpermanently\add* amongÂŠ350527 them.â â
\c 38
\ms1 The defeat of all of Yisrael's opponents
