\s1 Invasion by Gog and his army
\rem /s1 Gog as the Instrument of God; A Message for Gog; A Prophecy Against Gog; Invasion by Gog
\p
\v 1 Then YahwehÂŠ350534 \add âgave\add* me \add another\add* messageÂŠ350532:
\v 2 âHumanity's child, \add âlook\add* toward the land of MagogÂŠ350547 \add ?where King\add* GogÂŠ350545 is the main leader of MeshekÂŠ350550 and Tuval, and prophesyÂŠ350552 againstÂŠ350543 him.\x + \xo 38:2: \xt Rev 20:8.\x*
\v 3 Tell him that the masterÂŠ350558 YahwehÂŠ350558 saysÂŠ350557 this: Listen, I'm againstÂŠ350561 youÂŠ350561, GogÂŠ350562, leader of MeshekÂŠ350565 andÂŠ350566 Tuval,
\v 4 \add âso\add* I'll turnÂŠ350568 you aroundÂŠ350568 and put hooksÂŠ350570 into your jaws. ThenÂŠ350568 I'll bringÂŠ350572 you out with all your army, horsesÂŠ350580, and horsemen, all of them dressed inÂŠ350571 full armourâa hugeÂŠ350586 group with largeÂŠ350586 and small shields, all of them holding swordsÂŠ350590.
\v 5 Persia, \add Ethiopia\add* (Kush), and Libya are with them, all of them with shieldsÂŠ350598 and helmetsÂŠ350599,
\v 6 \add as well as\add* GomerÂŠ350601 and all its troops, and Beyt-TogarmahÂŠ350606, from the far partsÂŠ350607 of the northÂŠ350608, and all its troops. Many peopleÂŠ350614 groups are with you.
\v 7 \add Tell Gog to\add* \add âget ready as commander, and to assembleÂŠ350624 and prepareÂŠ350618 his troops\add*.
\v 8 You'll be \add âsummoned many daysÂŠ350631 later\add*, then after some yearsÂŠ350635 you'll goÂŠ350636 to a land that's recovered from war and \add âwhere the people have come back from many nations\add*âgatheredÂŠ350644 back to Yisrael's mountainsÂŠ350648 that had continuouslyÂŠ350654 been a ruin. ButÂŠ350655 the land's people will \add indeed\add* be broughtÂŠ350657 out of the nations, and they'll all live \add there\add* safely \add again\add*.
\v 9 ThenÂŠ350662 you'll goÂŠ350664 \add âin like a stormÂŠ350663 with yourÂŠ350672 large army\add*âyou'll all be like a cloudÂŠ350665 coveringÂŠ350666 the land.
\p
\v 10 TheÂŠ350681 masterÂŠ350680 YahwehÂŠ350680 saysÂŠ350679 this: \add ButÂŠ350682\add* plans will \add start to\add* form in yourÂŠ350690 heartÂŠ350690 on that dayÂŠ350684 and you'll deviseÂŠ350691 wicked schemes.
\v 11 ThenÂŠ350695 you'll \add âthink\add*, âI'llÂŠ350696 \add take my army\add* up onto the open groundâ\add âwe'll attack\add* the people living quietly \add âand peacefullyÂŠ350702\add*âall of them living where thereÂŠ350711 are no walls or barriers, and no city gatesÂŠ350710.
\v 12 I'll capture booty and steal plunder \add âand use my forces\add* against those ruins thatÂŠ350727 have been newly inhabitedÂŠ350723, and against those people who've returned from the nationsÂŠ350728âpeople who are gaining livestockÂŠ350730 and propertyÂŠ350731, and who are living at the centreÂŠ350735 of the world.â
