\v 5 There was a wall surrounding the temple area. The measuring rod inÂŠ351617 the man's handÂŠ351617 was \add âjust over three metresÂŠ351623 long\add*. (It was sixÂŠ351621 long cubitsâeach long cubit was a cubit long plusÂŠ351617 a handbreadthÂŠ351625.) \add âSoÂŠ351610\add* he measured the wall, and it was one measuring rod thick and one high.\x + \xo 40:5â42:20: \xt 1Ki 6:1-38; 2Ch 3:1-9.\x*
