\v 42 There were four cut-stone tables for the burnt offerings, \add âeach just under a metre long and wide, and standing half a metre tall\add*. They kept the tools whichÂŠ352247 they used to slaughterÂŠ352248 the burnt offerings for the sacrificesÂŠ352253 onÂŠ352252 those \add stone\add* tables.
