\p
\v 44 Within the inner courtyardÂŠ352274 \add butÂŠ352269\add* on the outsideÂŠ352269 of the inner gate were singers' roomsÂŠ352272âone on the northern side facing south, andÂŠ352269 the other on the southern side facing north.
\v 45 ThenÂŠ352295 the man told me, âThis roomÂŠ352298 facing southÂŠ352302 is for the priestsÂŠ352303 who are on duty in the temple.
\v 46 The roomÂŠ352308 facing northÂŠ352312 is for the priestsÂŠ352313 on duty at the altarÂŠ352316, thatÂŠ352309 is, for Tsadok'sÂŠ352320 descendantsâthey're the \add only\add* Levites who approachÂŠ352321 YahwehÂŠ352327 to serveÂŠ352328 himÂŠ352328.â
\s1 The inner courtyard
\rem /s1 The Inner Courtyard and the Temple Building; The Inner Courtyard and Temple
\p
\v 47 Next he measuredÂŠ352330 the squareÂŠ352341 courtyardÂŠ352333 at fifty-four metres long andÂŠ352330 wideÂŠ352338, with the altarÂŠ352342 in frontÂŠ352343 of the temple.
\s1 The temple entrance
\rem /s1 The Temple
\p
\v 48 ThenÂŠ352346 the man took me to the temple porch and measuredÂŠ352351 its doorpostsâthey were each two and a half metres thick. The entryway itself was seven metresÂŠ352355 wide,\f + \fr 40:48 \ft Following the LXX, as the 1.5m (three cubits) in the Hebrew appears likely to be a copying mistake.\f* and the walls on each side of it were one and a half metres wide.
\v 49 The porchÂŠ352370 was eleven metres wide and six metres deep, \add withÂŠ352377\add* stepsÂŠ352377 going up to it and pillarsÂŠ352381 standing onÂŠ352377 each side of it.
\c 41
\s1 Inside the temple
\p
\v 1 ThenÂŠ352390 the man took me into the temple'sÂŠ352393 holy place andÂŠ352390 measuredÂŠ352394 the doorposts \add at\add* three metresÂŠ352400 thick on each side.
\v 2 The doorway was five metres wide \add and\add* the wall on each side was two and a half metres long. ThenÂŠ352413 the man measuredÂŠ352425 the dimensions of the holy placeâtwenty-one metres long and eleven metres wide.
\v 3 ThenÂŠ352433 the man wentÂŠ352433 into the \add very sacred\add* innerÂŠ352434 place and measuredÂŠ352435 the door at one metre wide, and the doorway was three metres wide. The walls on either side were nearly four metres wide.
\v 4 Then he measured the square room's lengthÂŠ352452 andÂŠ352449 widthÂŠ352455 of eleven metres, \add measuring\add* to the templeÂŠ352461 hallway. Then he saidÂŠ352462 to me, âThis is the most sacredÂŠ352465 area.â
\s1 The temple rooms
\rem /s1 The Rooms Built against the Temple Walls
\p
\v 5 ThenÂŠ352468 the man measuredÂŠ352468 the wall of the house at three metres thick. The widthÂŠ352474 of each side room around the house was two metres.
\v 6 There were side rooms on threeÂŠ352489 levels, one room above another, thirtyÂŠ352490 rooms on each level. There were ledgesÂŠ352492 around the temple wall to support all the side rooms, as the supports weren't built into the temple wall.
\v 7 SoÂŠ352510 the side rooms widened and went around going up, becauseÂŠ352515 the house went around higher and higher all aroundâthe rooms widened \add âon each higher level\add*, and a stairway went up through the middleÂŠ352538 level to the highest level.
\v 8 ThenÂŠ352540 I sawÂŠ352540 a raised part all around the temple, the foundationÂŠ352546 for the side roomsÂŠ352548. It measured a full rod in heightÂŠ352542â\add âjust over three metresÂŠ352552\add*.
\rem /s1 The Building on the West
\v 9 The width of the wallÂŠ352556 of the side rooms on the outside was two andÂŠ352565 a half metresÂŠ352564. There was an open spaceÂŠ352566 outside those rooms in the temple.
\v 10 On the other side of that open space were the priests' outer side roomsÂŠ352573. That space was eleven metres wide all around the temple.
\v 11 There were doors into the side rooms from another open spaceÂŠ352585 with one doorwayÂŠ352590 on the northÂŠ352589 side, andÂŠ352583 the other on the southÂŠ352592. The widthÂŠ352593 of that open area was two and a half metresÂŠ352597 all around.
\s1 The western side
\p
\v 12 The building thatÂŠ352603 faced the courtyard on the western sideÂŠ352608 was thirty-six metres wide. Its wallÂŠ352615 was two and a half metres thick all around, andÂŠ352602 it was forty-seven metres long.
\s1 The temple building measurements
\rem /s1 The Total Measurements of the Temple Building
\p
\v 13 ThenÂŠ352628 the man measured the temple as being fifty-four metres long. The separateÂŠ352635 buildingÂŠ352636, itsÂŠ352637 wall, andÂŠ352628 the courtyard \add combined\add* also measured fifty-four metres \add âacross\add*.
\v 14 The widthÂŠ352642 of the front of the courtyard in front of the temple was also fifty-four metres.
\p
\v 15 ThenÂŠ352650 the man measuredÂŠ352650 the lengthÂŠ352651 of the buildingÂŠ352653 behindÂŠ352661 the templeÂŠ352668, to itsÂŠ352662 west, and includingÂŠ352662 the galleriesÂŠ352662 on either side, itÂŠ352661 came to fifty-four metres.
\rem /s1 Details of the Temple Building
\p The sacred innerÂŠ352669 placeÂŠ352657 and the porchÂŠ352670,
\v 16 the inner walls and the windows, includingÂŠ352674 the narrowÂŠ352675 windows, and the galleriesÂŠ352676 all around on threeÂŠ352679 levels, were all panelledÂŠ352682 in wood.
\v 17 Above the entryway to the innerÂŠ352701 sanctuary and spaced along the walls there was a \add ârepeating\add* pattern.
\v 18 It was decorated with winged creatures and palm treesÂŠ352717âwith a palm treeÂŠ352718 betweenÂŠ352719 each winged creature, and each winged creature had twoÂŠ352723 facesÂŠ352724:
\v 19 the humanÂŠ352728 face looked toward a palm tree on one side, andÂŠ352727 the youngÂŠ352735 lion face looked toward a palm tree on the other side. They were carved all around the entireÂŠ352743 temple.
\v 20 From the groundÂŠ352750 to above the doorway, winged creatures and palmÂŠ352756 treesÂŠ352756 were carved on the outer wallÂŠ352758 of the templeÂŠ352759.
\v 21 The door posts of the \add âmain templeÂŠ352762 roomÂŠ352766\add* were squareÂŠ352764, all with the same appearance.
\rem /s1 The Wooden Altar
\v 22 The wooden altarÂŠ352770 was one metre on each side and stood one and a half metresÂŠ352773 highÂŠ352774. Its cornerÂŠ352779 posts, base, and frame were \add all\add* made of wood.
\p Then the man said to me, âThis is the tableÂŠ352787 thatÂŠ352788 stands \add âin Yahweh'sÂŠ352790 presence\add*.â
\s1 The temple doorways
\rem /s1 The Doors
\p
\v 23 Both the main roomÂŠ352795 andÂŠ352795 the sacred placeÂŠ352795 had doubleÂŠ352792 doorsÂŠ352793â
\v 24 each consisting of two parts that swung on hinges.
\v 25 There were carvings of winged creatures and palmÂŠ352817 treesÂŠ352817 on the doorsÂŠ352814, just like on the wallsÂŠ352820, and there was a wooden roof over the frontÂŠ352825 porchÂŠ352826.
\v 26 There were narrow windowsÂŠ352829 and palmÂŠ352831 treesÂŠ352831 on either side of the porchÂŠ352837, like the side roomsÂŠ352838 of the temple, and they also had overhanging roofs.
\c 42
\s1 Two buildings near the temple
\rem /s1 Rooms for the Priests; The Holy Chambers and the Outer Wall; Two Buildings Near the Temple
\p
\v 1 Next the man sent me out to the outer courtyard on the northern side, and he broughtÂŠ352850 me to rooms in front of the outer courtyard and the northern outer wall.
\v 2 That building with a north-facing entranceÂŠ352872 was fifty-four metres long andÂŠ352874 twenty-seven metres wide.
\v 3 Some of those rooms faced the innerÂŠ352882 courtyard and were eleven metres away from the sanctuary. There were threeÂŠ352894 levels of rooms, and the ones above looked down onÂŠ352894 the ones below and were open to them, having a walkway. Some of the rooms looked out onto the outerÂŠ352887 courtyard.
\v 4 A five metre wide passageÂŠ352898 ran in frontÂŠ352896 of the rooms andÂŠ352908 was fifty-four\f + \fr 42:4 \ft The Hebrew text seemed to be missing a word here (as it didn't make sense), so the word from the (approx. 300 B.C.) Septuagint translation was used.\f* metresÂŠ352900 long. The rooms' doors \add âfaced\add* northÂŠ352909.
\v 5 ButÂŠ352911 the upperÂŠ352912 halls were smaller, becauseÂŠ352914 the walkways \add âthere used\add* more space than theyÂŠ352916 did in the bottom andÂŠ352920 middleÂŠ352920 levels of the building.
\v 6 \add @The third storey halls\add* had no pillarsÂŠ352929 (unlike the courtyardsÂŠ352930), so \add @the rooms at the highest level\add* were smaller than those on the bottom and middleÂŠ352936 levels.
\v 7 The outsideÂŠ352942 wall ran along the rooms toward the outerÂŠ352947 courtyardÂŠ352946 thatÂŠ352940 was in frontÂŠ352950 of the rooms, \add andÂŠ352939\add* was twenty-seven metres longÂŠ352952.
\v 8 The \add row of\add* rooms along the outerÂŠ352962 courtyardÂŠ352961 was twenty-seven metres long, andÂŠ352965 the \add row of\add* rooms facing the sanctuary was fifty-four metres long.
\v 9 There was an entrance to the lowest rooms from the easternÂŠ352979 side, coming from the outerÂŠ352983 courtyardÂŠ352982.
\v 10 There was \add also a set of\add* roomsÂŠ352999 along the outer courtyard wall on the easternÂŠ352990 side of the outer courtyard, in frontÂŠ352993 of the sanctuary's inner courtyard,
\v 11 with a walkway in frontÂŠ353002 of them. They \add âlooked similar to\add* the roomsÂŠ353004 on the northernÂŠ353007 side and had the same \add âmeasurements\add*, as well as the same exitsÂŠ353012 and arrangementsÂŠ353013 and doors.
\v 12 There were also doorways into rooms on the southÂŠ353020 side thatÂŠ353018 were similarÂŠ353016 to what was on the north side. There was an inside passage withÂŠ353022 an outer doorâthe passage had doors into all the rooms. At the easternÂŠ353029 end of the passage there was a door from the outside.
\p
\v 13 ThenÂŠ353032 the man told me, âThe northernÂŠ353035 rooms and the southernÂŠ353037 rooms thatÂŠ353038 are in frontÂŠ353041 of the outer courtyardÂŠ353042 are sacred rooms whereÂŠ353047 the priestsÂŠ353051 who work nearest to YahwehÂŠ353055 may eat the very sacred food. They'll put the very sacred things thereâthe food offering, the sin offering, and the guiltÂŠ353065 offeringâbecauseÂŠ353066 it's a very sacred area.
\v 14 When the priestsÂŠ353071 enterÂŠ353070 it, they must not goÂŠ353074 \add back\add* out of the sacred area to the outerÂŠ353079 courtÂŠ353078, without laying aside the clothes in which they servedÂŠ353085, since those \add âĄclothes\add* are sacred. So they must dress in otherÂŠ353094 clothes before going \add âback into the public areas\add*.â
\s1 Measuring outside the temple
\rem /s1 The Measurements of the Temple Area
\p
\v 15 The man completedÂŠ353101 measuring the temple interior and thenÂŠ353101 took me out to the easternÂŠ353113 gateÂŠ353109 and measured all the surrounding area there.
\v 16-19 He measured each sideÂŠ353120 \add of the wall\add* withÂŠ353122 \add &his\add* measuring rod, \add and it was\add* 270m\f + \fr 42:16 \ft Following the Septuagint here, which seems more accurate (unless he now has a shorter measuring rod).\f* long onÂŠ353122 each of the easternÂŠ353121, northern, southern, and western sides.
\v 20 \add âSo\add* the fourÂŠ353168 sidesÂŠ353169 that were measuredÂŠ353170 (and thus the wall around it) was 270m on each side, and the wall separatedÂŠ353182 the sacredÂŠ353184 area from the \add âpublic area\add*.
\c 43
\s1 The powerful splendour of God there to temple
\rem /s1 The Lord Returns to the Temple; The Divine Glory Returns to the Temple; The Lord's Glory Returns; The Glory Returns to the Temple
\p
\v 1 ThenÂŠ353187 the man took me to the gate thatÂŠ353192 opened to the east.
\v 2 Wow! The splendourÂŠ353198 of Yisrael'sÂŠ353200 godÂŠ353199 \add âappeared towards\add* the east. His voiceÂŠ353204 was like the \add âroar of rushing waterÂŠ353206\add*, andÂŠ353197 the land shone with his \add âbrilliance\add*.\x + \xo 43:2: \xt Eze 10:3-4,18-19; 11:22-23; Rev 1:15.\x*
\v 3 \add âWhat I saw in this vision was like what I'd seen in my earlier\add* visionsÂŠ353225, first by the KebarÂŠ353233 Canal, thenÂŠ353212 later when he\f + \fr 43:3 \ft It's only one letter difference, but the Hebrew has âIâ here which seems wrong and is adjusted in some later manuscripts.\f* came to destroyÂŠ353221 \add @Yerushalem\add*. I fell to \add my knees withÂŠ353220\add* my faceÂŠ353237 \add to the ground\add*.
\v 4 \add âSoÂŠ353239\add* Yahweh'sÂŠ353240 \add âbrightness\add* entered into the temple via the easternÂŠ353250 entrance.
\p
\v 5 ThenÂŠ353252 the spiritÂŠ353253 liftedÂŠ353252 me up and broughtÂŠ353254 me into the innerÂŠ353258 courtÂŠ353257, and wow, Yahweh'sÂŠ353263 brilliance was filling the temple.
\v 6 ThenÂŠ353266 as the manÂŠ353270 was standingÂŠ353272 \add there\add* besideÂŠ353273 me, I heardÂŠ353266 someone speak to me from inside the temple,
\v 7 and \add @the voice\add* told me, âHumanity's child, this is the placeÂŠ353311 \add where I'll sit onÂŠ353308\add* my throneÂŠ353283 and \add ârest\add* my feetÂŠ353288âwhereÂŠ353289 I'll live inÂŠ353308 the middleÂŠ353293 of the IsraeliÂŠ353294 peopleÂŠ353294 foreverÂŠ353297. Yisrael's \add âdescendants\add* and their kings will no longer profane my sacredÂŠ353305 name with their faithlessness or with the corpsesÂŠ353309 of their kings atÂŠ353308 their \add âhilltop shrines\add*.
\v 8 They'll no longer profane my sacred name by putting their \add âentrance\add* next to my \add âentrance\add*, and their doorposts next to my doorposts, with nothing butÂŠ353318 a wall between me and them. They profaned my sacred name with their disgusting actions, so I \add âdestroyedÂŠ353333\add* them with my angerÂŠ353335.
\v 9 Now they're to remove their prostitutionÂŠ353341 and \add ?their kings' corpsesÂŠ353342\add* from inÂŠ353346 front of me, and I'llÂŠ353345 live \add âamongÂŠ353346 them\add* foreverÂŠ353347.
\p
\v 10 âHumanity's child, \add âdescribe that temple to the IsraeliÂŠ353357 people\add* so they'll be ashamedÂŠ353363 of theirÂŠ353364 \add âdisobedience\add* andÂŠ353365 \add ?âthink about those plans\add*.
\v 11 If they're ashamedÂŠ353372 of everything they've doneÂŠ353376, then reveal the design of that temple to themâits details, its entrancesÂŠ353381 and exitsÂŠ353380, its complete design, and all its decrees and rules. ThenÂŠ353370 \add right\add* \add âin front of them,\add* writeÂŠ353400 that down so they'll see its complete design and all its rules, and then obey them.
\v 12 This is the regulation for the temple: From the peak of the hillÂŠ353422 to all the surrounding border around it, it'll be very sacredÂŠ353429. Listen, that's the regulation for the temple.
\s1 The altar dimensions
\rem /s1 The Altar
\p
\v 13 These are the altar's measurements, using the same kind of measuring rod that was used for the temple area: There's a gutterÂŠ353444 around the altar that's \add both\add* half a metre deep andÂŠ353437 wide. There's a rim around it that's 23cm wide. That'll be the base for \add the rest of\add* the altar.\x + \xo 43:13-17: \xt Exo 27:1-2; 2Ch 4:1.\x*
\v 14 The lower part of the gutterÂŠ353460 is one metre high to the lower ledge that surrounds the altar. The lower ledge is half a metre wide. From that ledge to the upper ledge, it's twoÂŠ353466 metresÂŠ353467. That ledge is also half a metre wide.
\v 15 The altarÂŠ353482 body \add at the top\add* is another two metresÂŠ353484 high andÂŠ353482 has a \add âhornlike projection\add* jutting up \add from each of its corners\add*.
\v 16 The sidesÂŠ353503 of the squareÂŠ353500 body are six metres long.
\v 17 The upper ledgeÂŠ353505 that bordersÂŠ353515 the altar body is also a square, eight metres long onÂŠ353509 each side, andÂŠ353505 has a rim all around that's 27cm wide. There's a gutterÂŠ353520 measuring half a metre atÂŠ353509 the bottom of the altar. There are stepsÂŠ353525 leading up to the east side of the altar.â
\s1 The purification of the new altar
\rem /s1 The Consecration of the Altar
\p
\v 18 ThenÂŠ353529 \add @the man\add* told me, âHumanity's child, the masterÂŠ353536 YahwehÂŠ353536 saysÂŠ353535 that those are the dimensions for when they make the altarÂŠ353540 for presenting the burntÂŠ353545 offeringÂŠ353543 on, andÂŠ353546 for sprinklingÂŠ353546 bloodÂŠ353548 onto.\x + \xo 43:18-27: \xt Exo 29:35-37.\x*
\v 19 You mustÂŠ353550 giveÂŠ353550 a bullÂŠ353565 from the cattle as a sinÂŠ353569 offeringÂŠ353569 for the LeviticalÂŠ353554 priestsÂŠ353553 who are Tsadok'sÂŠ353558 descendantsâthose who approach me to serveÂŠ353564 me. That's the masterÂŠ353562 Yahweh'sÂŠ353563 declaration.
\v 20 ThenÂŠ353571 you'll takeÂŠ353571 some of \add @the bull's\add* bloodÂŠ353572 and place it on the altar's âhornsÂŠ353577â and on the four top edges and the surrounding rim. You'll purifyÂŠ353587 it and \add âmake it allowable in my presence\add*.
\v 21 ThenÂŠ353591 takeÂŠ353591 that sinÂŠ353594 offeringÂŠ353594 bullÂŠ353593 andÂŠ353595 burnÂŠ353595 itÂŠ353595 inÂŠ353596 the designated part of the temple area outsideÂŠ353598 the sanctuaryÂŠ353599.
\v 22 ThenÂŠ353601 onÂŠ353601 the secondÂŠ353602 dayÂŠ353601, you'll get from the goatsÂŠ353606 a male goatÂŠ353604 without any blemishes, andÂŠ353601 offer it as a sin offeringÂŠ353608âthe priests will purify the altarÂŠ353612 just as they purified it withÂŠ353601 the bullÂŠ353615.
\v 23 When you finishÂŠ353617 that purificationÂŠ353618, offer an unblemished bullÂŠ353620 from the cattle and an unblemished ram from the flockÂŠ353628,
\v 24 and offer them to \add me,\add* Yahweh. The priestsÂŠ353635 will throwÂŠ353634 salt onto them and presentÂŠ353631 them as a burntÂŠ353640 offeringÂŠ353640 to Yahweh.
\v 25 Then every dayÂŠ353649 for \add the next\add* seven daysÂŠ353644 youÂŠ353645 must bring a billy goatÂŠ353646 to the priest to be sacrificed for an offeringÂŠ353648, so I'll accept the altar. You must also sacrifice a youngÂŠ353651 bullÂŠ353650 and a ram, each without any defect, that the priests will provide.
\v 26 They must atoneÂŠ353663 for the altarÂŠ353666 for seven daysÂŠ353662 and purifyÂŠ353667 it, and in that way they must consecrate it \add to me\add*.
\v 27 \add âAfter doing all that\add*, from the eighthÂŠ353680 dayÂŠ353679 onwardÂŠ353681 the priestsÂŠ353683 will prepare you \add people\add*'s burntÂŠ353689 offerings and your peaceÂŠ353692 offerings onÂŠ353679 the altarÂŠ353686, and I'llÂŠ353693 acceptÂŠ353693 youÂŠ353694. That's the masterÂŠ353696 Yahweh'sÂŠ353697 declaration.â
\c 44
\s1 The locked doorway
\rem /s1 The Prince, the Levites, the Priests; The Use of the East Gate; The Prince, Levites, and Priests; The Closed Gate
\p
\v 1 Then the man took me back to the outerÂŠ353705 sanctuaryÂŠ353704 gateÂŠ353703 facing east, \add âbutÂŠ353700\add* it was shut,
\v 2 andÂŠ353711 Yahweh told me, âThis gateÂŠ353714 has been sealed shutâit won'tÂŠ353718 be openedÂŠ353719. No person will goÂŠ353723 through it, becauseÂŠ353725 Yisrael's godÂŠ353727 Yahweh entered through it, so it's \add now\add* closed.
\v 3 \add Only Yisrael's\add* ruler will sit by it to eat foodÂŠ353745 \add âin frontÂŠ353748 of\add* YahwehÂŠ353749, \add butÂŠ353754\add* he'll enter via the gate's porchÂŠ353751, and leave the same way.â
\s1 Foreigners disallowed in the temple
\rem /s1 Rules for Admission to the Temple; Admission to the Temple
\p
\v 4 ThenÂŠ353757 he took me to the frontÂŠ353764 of the temple by way of the northernÂŠ353761 gate, and I lookedÂŠ353766, and wow, Yahweh'sÂŠ353771 brilliance filledÂŠ353768 \add *his\add* temple, and I fell to \add my knees with\add* my face \add bowed towards the ground\add*.
\v 5 ThenÂŠ353781 Yahweh told me, âHumanity's child, \add âpay attention\add* and lookÂŠ353789 with your eyesÂŠ353790 and listenÂŠ353792 with your earsÂŠ353791 to everything that I'm declaring to you: all the instructionsÂŠ353802 about Yahweh'sÂŠ353783 temple and all its regulationsÂŠ353802. \add âTake special note of\add* the temple's entranceÂŠ353812 and exitsÂŠ353815.
\v 6 ThenÂŠ353818 tell the rebelliousÂŠ353821 \add âIsraelisÂŠ353824\add* that the masterÂŠ353828 YahwehÂŠ353828 saysÂŠ353827 this: Let all yourÂŠ353835 disgusting actions be enoughÂŠ353830 for youÂŠ353832 IsraeliÂŠ353824 peopleâ
\v 7 that you broughtÂŠ353839 foreignersÂŠ353842 with uncircumcised heartsÂŠ353845 and uncircumcised fleshÂŠ353847 to be inÂŠ353849 my sanctuaryÂŠ353849, profaningÂŠ353850 my temple, while you \add people\add* were offeringÂŠ353854 me food, fat, and bloodÂŠ353859. You \add people\add* have brokenÂŠ353860 my agreementÂŠ353863 with all your disgusting actions.
\v 8 You haven't carried out your duties regarding my sacred thingsÂŠ353872, butÂŠ353869 \add instead,\add* you \add people\add* appointedÂŠ353873 others to take up your duties, andÂŠ353873 you assigned them to care for my sacred place.
\p
\v 9 âThe masterÂŠ353882 YahwehÂŠ353882 saysÂŠ353881 this: No foreigner, from any of those who live among the IsraeliÂŠ353906 peopleÂŠ353905, may enter my sacred place if they're not physically circumcised or if they \add âhaven't declared themself to be one of my people\add*.
\s1 Demotion of the Levites
\rem /s1 The Levites Are Excluded from the Priesthood
\p
\v 10 TheÂŠ353916 LevitesÂŠ353911 went far from meâwandering away from me \add and\add* going afterÂŠ353920 their idolsÂŠ353921, butÂŠ353922 they'll be punishedÂŠ353923.
\v 11 They're \add still\add* servants in my sanctuaryÂŠ353926, watching the temple gatesÂŠ353931 and serving inside, and they slaughterÂŠ353938 the burntÂŠ353941 offeringsÂŠ353941 and the people's sacrificesÂŠ353944, and they'll standÂŠ353947 in front of the people and serveÂŠ353949 them.
\v 12 \add However,\add* because they sacrificed to their idolsÂŠ353956, they became sinful stumblingÂŠ353961 blocksÂŠ353961 for the \add âIsraeliÂŠ353958 people\add*, thereforeÂŠ353963 I've \add âpromised to take action\add* against them, and they'll \add âpay for their disobedience\add*. That's the masterÂŠ353970 Yahweh'sÂŠ353971 declaration.
\v 13 They mustn't come near to me to act as my priestsÂŠ353979 or to approach any of my sacred things, the most sacred things. Instead, they'll bear their shameÂŠ353992 andÂŠ353975 their guilt for the disgusting things they've done,
\v 14 butÂŠ353997 I'llÂŠ353997 place them as housekeepersÂŠ354001 in the templeâfor all its \add mundane\add* duties andÂŠ353997 \add âall the menial workÂŠ354003\add* that's doneÂŠ354006 in it.
\s1 The priests descendants of Saduk
\rem /s1 The Levitical Priests; The Priests
\p
\v 15 Then the LeviticalÂŠ354011 priestsÂŠ354010, those descendants of TsadokÂŠ354013 who fulfilled the duties of my sanctuaryÂŠ354019 when the IsraeliÂŠ354021 peopleÂŠ354021 were wandering away from me, they'll approach me to worship me. They'll standÂŠ354029 inÂŠ354020 front of me to offerÂŠ354031 me the fat and the bloodÂŠ354034. That's the masterÂŠ354036 Yahweh'sÂŠ354037 declaration.
\v 16 They'll comeÂŠ354040 to my sanctuaryÂŠ354043 and approach my tableÂŠ354048 to worship me and to fulfill their duties to me.
\v 17 WhenÂŠ354055 they come to the gates of the inner courtyard, they'll have to dress in linenÂŠ354063 clothingÂŠ354062, because they mustn't \add âwear\add* wool insideÂŠ354074 the courtyard gates or in the temple.\x + \xo 44:17-18: \xt Exo 28:39-43; Lev 16:4.\x*
\v 18 \add âThey mustÂŠ354078 wear\add* linen turbans onÂŠ354090 their headsÂŠ354081 and linen underclothesÂŠ354082 around their waistsÂŠ354087. They mustn't dress inÂŠ354090 clothing that makes them sweatÂŠ354090.
\v 19 WhenÂŠ354092 they go \add back\add* out to the outer courtyardÂŠ354095 to go \add back again\add* to the people, they must take off the clothes they wore when they servedâthey must take them off andÂŠ354092 lay them down inÂŠ354092 a sacred room, so they don'tÂŠ354120 make otherÂŠ354119 people sacred by contact withÂŠ354092 their special clothing.\x + \xo 44:19: \xt Lev 16:23.\x*
\p
\v 20 \add @The priests\add* mustn't shaveÂŠ354130 their heads or allow their hair to hang loosely, butÂŠ354128 they mustÂŠ354130 \add âkeep the hair on their heads neatly trimmed\add*.
\v 21 No priestÂŠ354146 should drinkÂŠ354143 wine \add âbefore\add* he comes to the innerÂŠ354151 courtÂŠ354150.\x + \xo 44:21: \xt Lev 10:9.\x*
\v 22 \add âAlsoÂŠ354166, priests can'tÂŠ354155 marry widows of men who weren't priests, or women who've been divorcedÂŠ354154âthey're permitted to marry only IsraeliÂŠ354165 women who've never been married, or widows of other priests\add*.
\p
\v 23 They mustÂŠ354177 teach the peopleÂŠ354176 the difference between things that are sacredÂŠ354179 and things that are not, and teach them how to know what things are acceptable to me and what things are not.\x + \xo 44:23: \xt Lev 10:10.\x*
\v 24 In a disputeÂŠ354189 they must judgeÂŠ354192 inÂŠ354194 accordance withÂŠ354194 my instructionsÂŠ354203 and regulationsÂŠ354203. They must keep my law and my statutes atÂŠ354194 every religious celebration, and they must observeÂŠ354207 my sacred rest days.
\p
\v 25 \add @Priests\add* mustn't defile themselves by going near a person's dead body. However, if the dead person was his fatherÂŠ354223 or motherÂŠ354224, son or daughterÂŠ354226, or brotherÂŠ354227 or unmarried sisterÂŠ354228, thenÂŠ354213 they can defile themselves,
\v 26 andÂŠ354237 afterÂŠ354237 they've been purifiedÂŠ354238, they mustÂŠ354241 \add âwait\add* for sevenÂŠ354239 daysÂŠ354240.
\v 27 ThenÂŠ354245 \add after that\add*, \add âwhen\add* he goesÂŠ354246 into the innerÂŠ354253 courtyardÂŠ354252 to serveÂŠ354254 inÂŠ354245 the sacredÂŠ354249 place, he mustÂŠ354256 bringÂŠ354256 a sinÂŠ354257 offeringÂŠ354257 for himself. That's the masterÂŠ354259 Yahweh'sÂŠ354260 declaration.
\p
\v 28 \add âThe priests mustÂŠ354262 not ownÂŠ354267 any land\add*âI am their inheritance andÂŠ354262 I'll be their property.\x + \xo 44:28: \xt Num 18:20.\x*
\v 29 They'll have the food offerings, the sinÂŠ354277 offerings, and the guiltÂŠ354278 offerings to eatÂŠ354280, plusÂŠ354277 everything inÂŠ354284 YisraelÂŠ354284 that's devotedÂŠ354283 to Yahweh will be theirs.\x + \xo 44:29-30: \xt Num 18:8-19.\x*
\v 30 The best of the firstfruits \add âfrom every harvest\add* and every contributionÂŠ354295 \add from the people\add* will belongÂŠ354300 to the priests, and you \add Israelis\add* will give the first of your \add bread\add* doughÂŠ354302\f + \fr 44:30 \ft Probably after it's cooked???\f* to the priests so that blessingÂŠ354306 may rest on your home.
