\p
\v 1 When you throw dice to divide up the land as an inheritanceÂŠ354330 \add for the tribes\add*, you mustÂŠ354331 make an offering of land to YahwehÂŠ354333. That offering will become a sacred part of the land: \add âthirteen kilometres by ten kilometres inÂŠ354326 size\add*.\f + \fr 45:1 \ft The âten kilometresâ (twenty thousand cubits) from the Septuagint appears to correct the Hebrew which has half of that, but then v3 and v4 wouldn't make sense.\f* \add âThat entireÂŠ354350 area\add* will become sacred.
\v 2 \add âWithin that area,\add* a 270m wide squareÂŠ354364 area that'll surround the sacredÂŠ354359 placeÂŠ354359 \add âwill be left empty\add*, withÂŠ354362 a further border around it twenty-seven metres wide.
\v 3 Inside that \add first, larger\add* area, measureÂŠ354376 a \add rectangle\add* thirteen kilometres by fiveÂŠ354378 kilometres for the sanctuaryÂŠ354388âthe most sacredÂŠ354389 placeÂŠ354389.
\v 4 It'll be a sacred place in the nation for the priestsÂŠ354397 who serve Yahweh, who come near Yahweh to serve him. It'll be a place for their housesÂŠ354409 and a sacred area for the sacred place.
\v 5 The \add other half\add*, which is \add also\add* thirteen kilometres long andÂŠ354413 fiveÂŠ354413 kilometres wide, will be for towns for the LevitesÂŠ354422 who serveÂŠ354423 in the temple.
\p
\v 6 You'll designate an area thirteen kilometres long by half a kilometre wide for the city that will be next to the area reserved for the holy place. This city will belongÂŠ354447 to all the \add âIsraeliÂŠ354445 people\add*.
