\p
\v 10 You \add Israelis\add* must \add âuse accurate scales and measuring containers\add*.\x + \xo 45:10: \xt Lev 19:36.\x*
\v 11 \add âThe baskets for measuring dry things and containersÂŠ354549 for measuring liquids (called an âefahâ for dry things and a âbathâ for liquids, both a tenth of the large 220 litre âhomerâ) must be the same volumeâeach must hold twenty-two litres\add*.
\v 12 \add âFor weights, the shekel weight mustÂŠ354563 be tenÂŠ354570 grams. (Twenty âgerahsÂŠ354564â makes one shekel, thenÂŠ354562 sixty shekels makes one âminaâ.)\add*
\rem /s1 Special Offerings and Celebrations; Offerings; Offerings and Holy Days
\p
\v 13 You \add Israelis\add* mustÂŠ354578 present \add to the leader\add* \add âone measure of wheatÂŠ354584 or barleyÂŠ354588 for every sixty measures\add* \add thatÂŠ354579 youÂŠ354580 harvest\add*,
\v 14 \add âone measure of oliveÂŠ354593 oil for every one hundred measures\add* \add that you produce\add*,
\v 15 plusÂŠ354620 one sheepÂŠ354608 or goat from the flockÂŠ354613 for every twoÂŠ354616 hundredÂŠ354616 animals from the watered regionsÂŠ354617 of YisraelÂŠ354618, to be used for any burntÂŠ354620 offering or peaceÂŠ354621 offering to make atonementÂŠ354622 for the people. That's the masterÂŠ354625 Yahweh'sÂŠ354626 declaration.
\p
\v 16 All the peopleÂŠ354629 inÂŠ354637 the country will give that contributionÂŠ354634 to Yisrael's leader.
\v 17 It'll be the leader's responsibility to supply the animals for the burnt offerings, the grain offerings, and the drinkÂŠ354645 offerings atÂŠ354646 the festivals and the new moon celebrations, and onÂŠ354646 the rest daysâall the \add âIsraeli people's\add* scheduled festivals. He'll provideÂŠ354656 for the sin offerings, the grain offerings, the burnt offerings, and the peaceÂŠ354668 offerings \add âto make the Israeli people right\add* \add withÂŠ354646 God\add*.
\s1 The festivals
