\p
\v 1 The masterÂŠ354806 YahwehÂŠ354806 says this: The easternÂŠ354812 gate of the innerÂŠ354810 courtyardÂŠ354809 will be shut for the six days of work, butÂŠ354818 it'll be opened on rest days and on the day of the new moon.
\v 2 The leader will enterÂŠ354825 the outer courtyard by the pathÂŠ354827 to that gate and its outsideÂŠ354830 porchÂŠ354828, and he'll standÂŠ354831 at the doorpostsÂŠ354834 of the inner gate while the priestsÂŠ354837 perform his burntÂŠ354840 offering and peaceÂŠ354843 offering. ThenÂŠ354825 he'll worshipÂŠ354844 \add âright there\add* at the inner gate and \add âthenÂŠ354825 leave again\add*, butÂŠ354825 the gate won'tÂŠ354851 be shut untilÂŠ354854 eveningÂŠ354856.
