\v 5 The grain offering that he gives with the ram is twenty-two litres \add of flour\add*, andÂŠ354884 with the lambsÂŠ354887 it should be as much as he pleases, along with one litre of \add olive\add* oil for every twenty-two litres of flour.
\v 6 On the dayÂŠ354895 of the new moonÂŠ354896 he mustÂŠ354906 offer a bullÂŠ354897, sixÂŠ354902 lambsÂŠ354903, andÂŠ354895 a ramâ\add âall without any defects\add*.
\v 7 He mustÂŠ354912 \add also\add* provideÂŠ354912 a grainÂŠ354913 offeringÂŠ354913 of twenty-two litres of flour with the bullÂŠ354909, the same with the ram, andÂŠ354908 as much as heÂŠ354912 wants with the lambsÂŠ354914, along with a litre of \add olive\add* oilÂŠ354918 with every twenty-two litres of flour.
\v 8 The leader entersÂŠ354922 by the path to the gateÂŠ354926 and its porchÂŠ354925, and he mustÂŠ354927 leave by the same path.
\p
\v 9 ButÂŠ354931 when the land's peopleÂŠ354932 come inÂŠ354931 frontÂŠ354935 of YahwehÂŠ354936 atÂŠ354931 the scheduledÂŠ354937 festivals, anyone entering through the north gate to worshipÂŠ354943 must leave through the south gate, andÂŠ354931 anyone entering through the south gate must leave through the north gate. No one is allowed to turn back to the gate through whichÂŠ354963 they entered, becauseÂŠ354967 everyoneÂŠ354932 must keep going straight ahead until they get out.
\v 10 The leader must be amongstÂŠ354973 them in theirÂŠ354973 midstÂŠ354973âwhen they go in, he must go in, andÂŠ354972 when they leave, he must leave.
\v 11 During the festivalsÂŠ354979 \add that you hold for me\add*, the king mustÂŠ354981 present twenty-two litres of flour along with a bullÂŠ354984 or a ram, andÂŠ354979 as much flour as he wants to with the lambsÂŠ354987, along with a litre of \add olive\add* oilÂŠ354990 with every twenty-two litres of flour.
\p
\v 12 When the leader gives a voluntary offering to YahwehÂŠ355005 (either a burnt offering or a peace offering), the easternÂŠ355012 gate will be openedÂŠ355006 for him. He'll offer his burnt offering or his peace offering just like he does on the rest dayÂŠ355022. Then he mustÂŠ354997 go out, and afterÂŠ355029 he's gone out, the gate will be shut.
\s1 The daily sacrifice
