\p
\v 19 Next the man broughtÂŠ355146 me through the entranceÂŠ355147 atÂŠ355147 the gateÂŠ355152 to the sacredÂŠ355156 roomsÂŠ355155 for the priestsÂŠ355159 whichÂŠ355148 were north-facing, andÂŠ355162 what's more, thereÂŠ355164 was a placeÂŠ355165 towardÂŠ355168 the west.
\v 20 He told me, âThat's the placeÂŠ355174 where the priestsÂŠ355179 must boil the guiltÂŠ355182 offering and the sinÂŠ355185 offering and where they must bake the grainÂŠ355190 offering. They mustn't bring the offerings into the outerÂŠ355196 courtyardÂŠ355195, because then the peopleÂŠ355200 would become sacredÂŠ355197 \add (and not be able to leave)\add*.â
\p
\v 21 ThenÂŠ355202 he broughtÂŠ355202 me to the outerÂŠ355206 courtyard and led me past the four corners of that courtyard, and I saw that inÂŠ355215 every corner of the courtyard there was \add another\add* \add âenclosed area\add*,
\v 22 and each was twenty-two metres long andÂŠ355228 sixteen metres wide.
\v 23 Around the inside of each of those enclosed areas was a stone ledge, with cooking hearthsÂŠ355241 \add all around\add* underÂŠ355243 the ledge.
\v 24 The man told me, âThose are the places whereÂŠ355252 the temple workers will boil the people'sÂŠ355261 sacrificesÂŠ355260.â
\c 47
\s1 The healing river
\rem /s1 The Stream Flowing from the Temple; The River From the Temple; The River of Healing; Water Flowing from the Temple
\p
\v 1 ThenÂŠ355263 the man took me back to the temple entranceÂŠ355266, and there was water flowing out from under the \add âfrontÂŠ355278 edge of the building\add* towardÂŠ355275 the east, and the water was flowing down the south sideÂŠ355284 of the temple, to the right of the altarÂŠ355288.\x + \xo 47:1: \xt Zech 14:8; Yhn 7:38; Rev 22:1.\x*
\v 2 SoÂŠ355290 he took me out through the northernÂŠ355294 gate and led me aroundÂŠ355295 \add the outsideÂŠ355297\add* to the easternÂŠ355304 gate, and look, the waterÂŠ355307 was flowing from this gate on its southÂŠ355312 side.
\v 3 As the manÂŠ355316 \add âstarted walking\add* toward the east holding his measuring line inÂŠ355322 his handÂŠ355319, he measured off five hundred metresÂŠ355322 and led me through the waterÂŠ355324, which was ankle-deep.
\v 4 ThenÂŠ355328 he measured another five hundred metres and led me throughÂŠ355336 the waterÂŠ355331, which was \add now\add* knee-deep, and thenÂŠ355328 after another five hundred metres it was \add âup to the waist\add*.
\v 5 FinallyÂŠ355346 he measuredÂŠ355340 off another five hundred metres, butÂŠ355340 the water had become deep enough to swim in andÂŠ355340 too deep to crossÂŠ355347âit was \add now\add* a river thatÂŠ355343 couldn't be walked throughÂŠ355358.
\v 6 The man \add âasked\add* me, âHumanity's child, \add âhave you taken note of all\add* this?â
\p ThenÂŠ355360 he led me out andÂŠ355360 had me \add âreturn\add* along the riverbankÂŠ355369.
\v 7 As I walked back, wow, \add now\add* the riverbankÂŠ355376 had many trees on each side.
\v 8 The man told me, âThis water \add âflows eastward and down into the Rift Valley\add*. \add *It'll\add* flow into the Dead Sea and will make it into freshÂŠ355402 water.
\v 9 \add âAs a result,\add* every kind of livingÂŠ355410 creatureÂŠ355409 that swarmsÂŠ355414 will live where that water flows. There'll be lots of fishÂŠ355424 when that water flows \add @into the Dead Sea\add* as it causes the salty water to becomeÂŠ355432 freshÂŠ355432 waterâeverything will live wherever that riverÂŠ355439 goes.
\v 10 ThenÂŠ355441 the fishermenÂŠ355445 from Eyn-Gedi will stand \add there\add* by the water, andÂŠ355441 there'll be a placeÂŠ355452 to dry out the fishing nets near Eyn-Eglaim. There'll be many kindsÂŠ355455 of fish in the Dead Seaâplentiful just like the fish in the Mediterranean Sea.
\v 11 \add However,\add* the Dead Sea's swamps and marshesÂŠ355466 won'tÂŠ355467 be made freshâthey'll be for providing salt.
\v 12 Beside that riverÂŠ355474 on both banksÂŠ355478, all kinds of fruit trees will grow. Their leaves will never wilt, and \add âthey'll never fail to fruit\add*â\add in fact\add* \add *they'll\add* bear fruit everyÂŠ355483 monthÂŠ355496 becauseÂŠ355498 that waterÂŠ355499 from the temple flows to them. Their fruit will be \add âgood to eat\add*, and theirÂŠ355499 leaves will \add âhelp with\add* healingÂŠ355510.\x + \xo 47:12: \xt Rev 22:2.\x*
\s1 Land boundaries
\rem /s1 Division of the land among the tribes; Boundaries for the Land; The New Boundaries of the Land; The Boundaries of the Land
\p
\v 13 The masterÂŠ355515 YahwehÂŠ355515 saysÂŠ355514 that this will be the way that youÂŠ355520 divide the land up for Yisrael's twelve tribesÂŠ355526: YosefÂŠ355528 \add (Joseph)\add* will have \add âa double allocation\add*.
\v 14 You're to equally divideÂŠ355531 \add the land\add* that I \add âtook action\add* to giveÂŠ355540 to yourÂŠ355541 ancestorsÂŠ355541â\add from now onÂŠ355546\add* that land will come to youÂŠ355545 \add Israelis\add* as an inheritanceÂŠ355546.
\p
\v 15 \add #These will be the land boundariesÂŠ355549\add*: On the northÂŠ355552 sideÂŠ355551, it'll extend from the Mediterranean Sea east along the road towards Hetlon, andÂŠ355548 thenÂŠ355548 on to TsedadÂŠ355560,
\v 16 to BerotahÂŠ355564, and then on to Sivrayim, which is on the border between DamascusÂŠ355570 and HamatÂŠ355573. The boundary will run as far as Hatser-Hattikon, which is on the border of the Havran \add region\add*.
\v 17 \add âSoÂŠ355582\add* the boundary will extend from the Mediterranean Sea to Hatsar-Enan on the borderÂŠ355589 between HamatÂŠ355595 to the north andÂŠ355582 DamascusÂŠ355590 \add to the south\add*. \add âThat'll be the northern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 18 On the eastern side, the boundary will extend between Havran and DamascusÂŠ355606, south along the YordanÂŠ355612 \add River\add* between the GileadÂŠ355608 \add regionÂŠ355610\add* and Yisrael'sÂŠ355611 territoryÂŠ355610, along the Dead Sea as far as Tamar.\f + \fr 47:18 \ft Tamar: the Hebrew has âthe Eastern Seaâ.\f* \add âThat'll be the eastern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 19 On the southern side, the boundary will extend from TamarÂŠ355626 to the springs near Merivat-KadeshÂŠ355631. ThenÂŠ355623 it'll extend \add west\add* along the brook of Egypt to the Mediterranean Sea. \add âThat'll be the southern boundary\add*.
\p
\v 20 On the western side, the boundaryÂŠ355648 will be the Mediterranean Sea, \add north\add* to a point near Levo-HamatÂŠ355653.
\p
\v 21 This is how you'll divideÂŠ355659 this land for yourselves among Yisrael's tribesÂŠ355665:
\v 22 You must assign the land as a permanent possession for yourselves and also for any foreigners who are living and raising their childrenÂŠ355679 among you. You must consider them to be like nativeÂŠ355683 born IsraelisÂŠ355684, and they must be assigned land among Yisrael's tribesÂŠ355690.
\v 23 Wherever foreigners are living, youÂŠ355701 mustÂŠ355701 giveÂŠ355701 them some land \add âto belong to them permanently\add*. That's the masterÂŠ355704 Yahweh'sÂŠ355705 declaration.â
\c 48
\s1 Land allocated to Yisrael's tribes
\rem /s1 Division of the Land; The Division of the Land; The Division of the Land among the Tribes; The Tribal Portions
\p
\v 1 Here's a list of Yisrael's tribes and the territory that each tribe is to receive. The northern boundary of Yisrael will start at the Mediterranean Sea and go \add east\add* to Hetlon \add city\add*, then to Levo-Hamat, and farther on to Hatsar-EnanÂŠ355724, which is \add south\add* of DamascusÂŠ355726, and it'll continue to Hamat. Each tribe will receive land that will extend from the easternÂŠ355737 boundary of Yisrael west to the Mediterranean Sea.
\rem /s1 The Special Section in the Center of the Land
\p The tribe of DanÂŠ355739 will receive land alongside Yisrael's northern borderÂŠ355725.
\v 2 \add âSouthÂŠ355745 of their area\add* will be the territory for the tribe of AsherÂŠ355753.
\v 3 \add âSouth of\add* Asher'sÂŠ355759 land will be territory for the tribe of NaftaliÂŠ355767.
\v 4 \add âSouth of\add* Naftali'sÂŠ355773 land will be territory for the tribe of Menashsheh.
\v 5 \add âSouth of\add* Menashsheh's land will be territory for the tribe of EfrayimÂŠ355795.
\v 6 \add âSouth of\add* Efrayim'sÂŠ355801 land will be territory for the tribe of Reuven.
\v 7 \add âSouth of\add* Reuven's land will be territory for the tribe of YehudahÂŠ355823 \add (Judah)\add*.
\s1 The chosen place
\p
\v 8 \add âSouth of\add* Yehudah'sÂŠ355828 land will be an area thatÂŠ355838 the entireÂŠ355840 nation will give to meâyou \add Israelis\add* will set it apart for special use. The temple will be inÂŠ355857 the middleÂŠ355857 of the area thatÂŠ355838's thirteen kilometres wide andÂŠ355826 as long as the other land allocations.
\p
\v 9 The specialÂŠ355859 area thatÂŠ355860 you \add Israelis\add* will give to YahwehÂŠ355862 will be thirteen kilometres long and fiveÂŠ355864 kilometres wide.
\v 10 This special area will be allocated to the priestsÂŠ355876: you'll assign them an area of land measuring thirteen kilometres on the northernÂŠ355877 and southernÂŠ355889 sides, and five kilometres on the westernÂŠ355881 and easternÂŠ355885 sides. Yahweh'sÂŠ355897 temple will be inÂŠ355898 the middleÂŠ355898 of that special area.
\v 11 The temple area will be for the priestsÂŠ355900, Tsadok'sÂŠ355903 descendants, who are dedicated to serving me. (They're the ones who served me faithfully and didn'tÂŠ355908 turn away \add from me\add* like the LevitesÂŠ355916 \add âand the others\add* did.)
\v 12 The \add âpriests' allocation\add* will be a portionÂŠ355922 of that very sacredÂŠ355922 land, extending to the Levites' borderÂŠ355928.
\v 13 The land assigned to the Levites will be the same size as the land that the priestsÂŠ355934 will receive. (SoÂŠ355931 together, these two portions of land will be thirteen kilometres long andÂŠ355931 about ten kilometres wide.)
\v 14 They mustn't sell or barter itânone of this best part of Yisrael's land mustÂŠ355954 ever be \add âused for any other purpose\add*, becauseÂŠ355963 it's all sacredÂŠ355965 to YahwehÂŠ355966.
\p
\v 15 Another strip of land thirteen kilometres long and almost three kilometres wide will be allotted for other people livingÂŠ355982 in the special area to use. They may build homes and have pasturelands there, and there'll be a city in the middleÂŠ355986 of thatÂŠ355970 area.
\v 16 The city \add âwill be square, over two kilometres long on each side\add*,
\v 17 with an open area around itÂŠ356020, within the special area, that will be about 130m wide in each direction.
\v 18 Outside the city, there'll be two strips that'll extend five kilometres onÂŠ356037 each of the east and west sides, and the produceÂŠ356053 from \add @those strips\add* will be food for the people working inÂŠ356037 the city.
\v 19 \add âThoseÂŠ356064 who come from the various tribesÂŠ356063 to work in the cityÂŠ356060 may also work in this farmland\add*.
\v 20 That entireÂŠ356076 special area, includingÂŠ356070 the land given for Yahweh's use and the cityÂŠ356084, will be a square that's thirteen kilometres long onÂŠ356072 each side.
\p
\v 21 The tracts of land to the east and to the west of Yahweh's area and the cityÂŠ356096 will belong to the leader. One area will extend thirteen kilometres east to Yisrael's easternÂŠ356108 boundary, and the other will extend thirteen kilometres west \add to the Mediterranean Sea\add*. Yahweh's area, whichÂŠ356086 contains the temple, will be inÂŠ356128 the middleÂŠ356128.
\rem /s1 Land for the Other Tribes
\v 22 TheÂŠ356132 area that belongsÂŠ356137 to the leader (that surrounds the LevitesÂŠ356132' property and the cityÂŠ356134 in the middleÂŠ356135 of it) will be between the tribe of YehudahÂŠ356142 \add to the north\add* and the tribe of BenyaminÂŠ356145 \add to the south\add*.
\p
\v 23 South of Yahweh's area, each of the other tribes will receive one section of land that extends from the easternÂŠ356152 \add boundary of Yisrael\add* west \add all the way to the Mediterranean Sea.\add*
\p Just south of Yahweh's area will be territory for the tribe of BenyaminÂŠ356158.
\v 24 \add âSouth of\add* Benyamin'sÂŠ356164 land will be the land for the tribe of Shimeon.
\v 25 \add âSouth of\add* Shimeon's land will be the land for the tribe of Yissakar.
\v 26 \add âSouth of\add* Yissakar's land will be the land for the tribe of Zevulun.
\v 27 \add âSouth of\add* Zevulun's land will be the land for the tribe of GadÂŠ356214.
\v 28 Gad'sÂŠ356219 southern boundary will extend from TamarÂŠ356227 \add south\add* to the watersÂŠ356228 of Merivah-KadeshÂŠ356230, and farther \add west\add* to the brook \add of Egypt\add*, and thenÂŠ356217 on to the Mediterranean Sea.
\p
\v 29 That \add describes\add* the territory you'llÂŠ356241 allocate to Yisrael's tribesÂŠ356243 to become theirÂŠ356246 permanent inheritanceÂŠ356242. That's the masterÂŠ356248 Yahweh'sÂŠ356249 declaration.
